WEBVTT

00:02.132 --> 00:04.439
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

00:18.148 --> 00:20.455
♪ Looking for my baby

00:20.629 --> 00:23.110
♪ Searching high
and looking low ♪

00:25.460 --> 00:28.245
♪ Oh been looking for my baby
this Christmas ♪

00:28.419 --> 00:30.465
♪ Just gotta let her know

00:33.816 --> 00:38.342
♪ All I want for Christmas
is to keep her from the cold ♪

00:41.084 --> 00:42.868
♪ Yeah I been rolling
on the river ♪

00:43.043 --> 00:45.132
♪ Been travelling
through the pines ♪

00:45.306 --> 00:48.700
♪ Been checking out the hills
and the beautiful coastline ♪

00:48.874 --> 00:50.876
♪ It's a Mississippi
Christmas ♪

00:51.051 --> 00:53.923
♪ All the family's gathered
round ♪

00:56.360 --> 00:58.841
♪ Yeah it's Christmas
in the Southland ♪

00:59.015 --> 01:01.496
♪ See the lights and hear
the sounds ♪

01:03.846 --> 01:07.806
♪ Santa's bringing Rudolph
Charlie Brown's got the tree ♪

01:07.980 --> 01:11.549
♪ Frosty's got his top hat
Just leave you here with me ♪

01:11.723 --> 01:13.682
♪ Nutcracker brought
the fruit cake ♪

01:13.856 --> 01:15.814
♪ Little Donner
is throwing down ♪

01:15.988 --> 01:18.861
♪ It's a wonderful life
'cause my baby's come to town ♪

01:42.537 --> 01:46.976
♪ You can soar with the eagle
with the dogs on the porch ♪

01:50.197 --> 01:56.507
♪ Yeah there's still a lot
of rebel and screw the North ♪

01:56.681 --> 02:00.076
♪ Oh it's a Mississippi
Christmas ♪

02:00.250 --> 02:02.905
♪ And my baby's here with me

02:05.255 --> 02:07.562
[ MUSIC ENDS ]

02:09.085 --> 02:10.391
Thanks for the ride.

02:31.847 --> 02:34.415
[ HUMMING ]

02:42.031 --> 02:43.075
And just who are you
trying to catch...

02:43.250 --> 02:45.687
under the mistletoe this year?

02:45.861 --> 02:49.212
White berries mean mistletoe,
red berries mean holly.

02:49.386 --> 02:51.693
You of all people should
know that!

02:51.867 --> 02:54.522
I thought I was picking you up
at the airport tomorrow.

02:54.696 --> 02:56.045
I caught an earlier
flight, so...

02:56.219 --> 02:57.525
I figured I'd surprise you.

02:57.699 --> 03:00.919
Oh, that's my kind of surprise,
welcome home, Holly!

03:01.093 --> 03:02.399
Good to see you, Momma.

03:02.573 --> 03:03.966
I can't believe you're
really here!

03:04.140 --> 03:06.055
I know, and for two full
weeks this time.

03:06.229 --> 03:09.841
It's a Christmas miracle. What
are you carrying in this thing?

03:10.015 --> 03:12.757
This cannot be good for your
back, and take that jacket off.

03:12.931 --> 03:13.802
You're gonna cook in that
down here.

03:13.976 --> 03:15.499
Okay, okay!

03:15.673 --> 03:16.979
I thought I'd get more of the
tree decorated...

03:17.153 --> 03:18.807
before you got here.

03:18.981 --> 03:21.375
But I guess we'll just have to
finish decorating it together.

03:21.549 --> 03:22.854
Sounds perfect.

03:23.028 --> 03:24.595
You must be hungry.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.162
I was just about to take
lunch...

03:26.336 --> 03:28.425
over to the festival volunteers
at Jones Park.

03:28.599 --> 03:29.774
You want to give me a hand?

03:29.948 --> 03:30.949
Yeah, of course.

03:31.123 --> 03:32.995
Got it all packed up
in the kitchen.

03:38.653 --> 03:40.785
Sure you don't want to put this
up, just in case?

03:40.959 --> 03:42.134
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:42.309 --> 03:43.527
That should be the last of it.

03:43.701 --> 03:45.486
I can't believe you still have
this pickup.

03:45.660 --> 03:47.966
Of course I do.

03:48.140 --> 03:49.838
It was your father's pride
and joy.

03:50.012 --> 03:51.970
I thought I was his pride
and joy.

03:52.144 --> 03:55.104
You were... he loved you just
as much as he loved his truck.

04:03.286 --> 04:06.028
I cannot wait for you to see
what they've done at the park.

04:06.202 --> 04:08.291
I'm excited.
You're gonna love it.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.641
You ready?
Yeah, let's do it.

04:10.815 --> 04:11.903
Okay.

04:12.948 --> 04:14.558
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

04:14.732 --> 04:15.690
Hold on.

04:19.302 --> 04:22.914
[ MUSIC FADES UP ]

05:10.310 --> 05:11.789
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

05:31.200 --> 05:33.115
You gotta be kidding me.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.131
Holly?
Hey, Mr. McGuire!

05:49.305 --> 05:50.872
It's so good to see you!

05:51.046 --> 05:54.615
Well, your momma said you were
comin' home for Christmas.

05:54.789 --> 05:57.226
She was real excited,
talks about you nonstop.

05:57.400 --> 05:58.749
That does not surprise me.

05:58.923 --> 06:00.795
I think the mailman knows
my shoe size.

06:00.969 --> 06:02.797
You bringing your famous fruit
stand back this year?

06:02.971 --> 06:04.102
Festival wouldn't
be the same without it.

06:04.276 --> 06:06.844
Yep, yep, it'll be there.
Good.

06:07.018 --> 06:09.281
I just got my location
assignment.

06:09.456 --> 06:11.240
Right next to your momma's
stand.

06:13.373 --> 06:15.940
Is she here?
Yeah.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.166
Hello, Caroline.

06:24.340 --> 06:25.820
Stuart.

06:25.994 --> 06:28.213
Just harvested a new crop of
sweet potatoes at the farm.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.911
Put some aside for you.

06:30.085 --> 06:32.827
Aw... that's mighty kind of you.

06:33.001 --> 06:37.179
Well, I did have a selfish
motivation.

06:37.353 --> 06:38.615
You promised me a slice...

06:38.789 --> 06:40.748
of the best sweet potato pie
in the county.

06:40.922 --> 06:44.055
Well, then... a promise
is a promise.

06:48.712 --> 06:52.020
What's up, Hollywood!
Benny!

06:52.194 --> 06:53.717
Good to see you!

06:53.891 --> 06:56.024
Nice to have you back!
We missed you 'round here!

06:56.198 --> 06:57.242
I missed you, babe.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.462
Hey, is that the brisket?

06:59.636 --> 07:02.073
I am so sorry, we've been
working since 5:00 AM...

07:02.247 --> 07:03.640
and I'm starving.

07:03.814 --> 07:05.773
How long does it take to set
everything up?

07:05.947 --> 07:08.950
Well, between the trees,
the stands and the lights...

07:09.124 --> 07:11.387
I'd say about a couple of weeks.
It's a massive set-up.

07:11.561 --> 07:13.650
Right outside, we got a bunch
of little elves.

07:13.824 --> 07:14.999
Well, do you guys need
some help?

07:15.173 --> 07:18.612
Oh, yes, we sure could
use some help.

07:18.786 --> 07:20.831
I'll let the boss man know
you offered.

07:21.005 --> 07:23.573
Mm-mm, oh, this is made
with love.

07:26.228 --> 07:27.708
Later, Hollywood!

07:36.586 --> 07:40.938
Are my eyes deceiving me...
or is that Holly Hart?

07:41.112 --> 07:42.853
Hi, Mike.

07:43.027 --> 07:45.203
I didn't know you were in town.

07:45.377 --> 07:46.466
I didn't tell you.

07:46.640 --> 07:49.381
It's been a long time.
Did you miss me?

07:49.556 --> 07:51.122
Oh, I can't say that I have.

07:52.515 --> 07:53.908
You stayin' with your momma?

07:54.082 --> 07:55.866
Maybe.

07:56.040 --> 07:58.390
Is uh-- is her number still
the same?

07:58.565 --> 07:59.914
Why would you need to call it?

08:00.088 --> 08:01.350
As soon as you ask me to.

08:01.524 --> 08:04.832
Hah, you're delusional.

08:05.006 --> 08:07.312
You still want to volunteer
at the festival, right?

08:07.487 --> 08:09.271
Yeah.

08:09.445 --> 08:12.100
Oh, lucky you... I happen to be
the project supervisor.

08:12.274 --> 08:14.711
How about I start you off
tomorrow morning...

08:14.885 --> 08:16.278
8:00 AM, bright and early?

08:16.452 --> 08:17.932
Sounds great.

08:20.412 --> 08:23.285
You know, they do say absence
makes the heart grow fonder.

08:23.459 --> 08:25.505
You sure you didn't miss me
a little bit?

08:25.679 --> 08:27.724
Let's give it a couple more
years.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.424
8:00 AM.

08:32.599 --> 08:36.037
Those boys sure do have an
appetite, cleaned me right out.

08:36.211 --> 08:37.604
All set?

08:37.778 --> 08:38.692
You didn't tell me the festival
was being run...

08:38.866 --> 08:40.694
by my ex-boyfriend.

08:40.868 --> 08:43.348
Did I forget to mention that?

08:43.523 --> 08:45.916
I know, he broke your heart.

08:46.090 --> 08:47.614
He didn't break my heart,
he just--

08:47.788 --> 08:50.051
But it would do you both
a lot of good...

08:50.225 --> 08:52.575
if you can just try to mend
fences while you're back.

08:52.749 --> 08:56.797
Give him a chance, maybe
you'll see a new side of him.

08:56.971 --> 08:59.103
Hm?

08:59.277 --> 09:00.322
Let's go.

09:08.591 --> 09:11.768
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

09:44.845 --> 09:46.107
[HOLLY] Smile.
[MIKE] I am smiling.

09:46.281 --> 09:47.804
[HOLLY] No, you're squinting.

09:47.978 --> 09:51.852
Well, I'm blinded by your
beauty... and slightly the sun.

09:52.026 --> 09:53.680
[ LAUGHING ]
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

09:55.159 --> 09:56.378
Perfect.

09:56.552 --> 09:57.466
Did you get my good side?

09:57.640 --> 10:00.121
They're all good.

10:04.516 --> 10:05.387
Let me see it.
No!

10:05.561 --> 10:07.215
Let me see it.
No! You'll shake it.

10:07.389 --> 10:08.651
No.

10:08.825 --> 10:11.088
You know what? Fine.
I don't wanna see it.

10:11.480 --> 10:15.832
Oh... Merry Christmas.

10:25.494 --> 10:27.409
Well, I figured since you'd be
joining me on campus soon...

10:27.583 --> 10:29.977
you should start dressing
the part.

10:33.023 --> 10:34.982
Look, I know this distance
hasn't been easy...

10:35.156 --> 10:36.723
but once we're in the same
place...

10:36.897 --> 10:38.899
it'll be a whole new beginning
for us.

10:42.598 --> 10:44.426
Do you like it?

10:48.386 --> 10:49.300
I love it.

10:53.478 --> 10:56.394
Here... hold it up.

10:56.568 --> 10:58.832
I want to take a picture.

10:59.006 --> 11:00.050
Yay!
What size is this?

11:00.224 --> 11:01.530
Stop.

11:11.496 --> 11:12.628
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

11:12.802 --> 11:14.499
I brought you some
fresh blankets.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.023
Not that you'll need them.

11:16.197 --> 11:18.155
Next few nights are supposed
to be some warm ones.

11:18.329 --> 11:20.462
Thanks, Momma.

11:20.636 --> 11:23.204
Oh, who's this?

11:23.378 --> 11:25.249
I found Rudolph here downtown.

11:25.423 --> 11:28.470
Hm, he's got a lot of miles
on him.

11:28.644 --> 11:31.168
I bet he means a lot
to someone out there.

11:31.342 --> 11:33.605
I know... I was gonna put
a picture online...

11:33.780 --> 11:34.911
see if I could find his owner.

11:35.085 --> 11:37.958
In fact... here, strike a pose.

11:40.395 --> 11:41.701
One, two, three.

11:41.875 --> 11:43.441
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

11:49.578 --> 11:51.406
All right, little guy...

11:51.580 --> 11:53.495
let's see if we can't get
you home for Christmas.

12:01.590 --> 12:03.853
Merry Christmas to you, Uncle,
and God save you!

12:04.027 --> 12:05.768
Bah humbug!

12:05.942 --> 12:07.814
[MAN] Christmas a humbug? You
can't mean that, I'm sure.

12:07.988 --> 12:09.598
[SCROOGE] I do mean it!
What did I miss?

12:09.772 --> 12:11.339
Nothing, it just came back
from commercial. You're good.

12:11.513 --> 12:12.862
Oh, good.

12:15.560 --> 12:16.997
No butter?

12:19.260 --> 12:20.740
It's for the tree.

12:20.914 --> 12:22.872
You're making me watch a movie
and not eat popcorn?

12:25.701 --> 12:27.398
This one's for you.

12:27.572 --> 12:29.270
Thanks, Momma.

12:34.057 --> 12:36.756
You know, it's only the two
of us for Christmas.

12:36.930 --> 12:39.889
It's okay if the tree doesn't
have a popcorn string.

12:40.063 --> 12:42.326
It's tradition.

12:42.500 --> 12:44.720
Yeah, I know, I just thought you
might want to take a break...

12:44.894 --> 12:48.202
from decorating and just relax
and watch the movie.

12:48.376 --> 12:51.596
Holly, for me, decorating the
house for Christmas...

12:51.771 --> 12:54.730
isn't a chore.

12:54.904 --> 12:57.080
It's something I look
forward to.

12:57.254 --> 13:02.216
It is Christmas... like when
I hang your stocking.

13:02.390 --> 13:05.262
I remember how you'd always
sneak downstairs...

13:05.436 --> 13:09.614
while your father and I were
asleep and open yours.

13:09.789 --> 13:14.532
Or when I make a wreath...

13:14.706 --> 13:18.362
takes me back to the time when
my momma first taught me how.

13:21.844 --> 13:23.672
I cherish every moment.

13:39.079 --> 13:39.601
[SCROOGE]
Good evening, sir.

13:52.222 --> 13:55.399
I bet it's really something
when it's all lit up, huh?

13:55.573 --> 13:58.750
It is. People used to come from
all over to see the show.

13:58.925 --> 14:02.276
Used to? Why did they stop?

14:02.450 --> 14:04.495
Hurricane... almost five years
ago.

14:04.669 --> 14:07.803
There was a storm surge, and the
entire town was underwater.

14:07.977 --> 14:09.936
This will be the first Winter
Festival since then.

14:10.110 --> 14:11.720
Oh my.

14:11.894 --> 14:15.245
Huh... well, they appear to have
made quite a recovery.

14:15.419 --> 14:16.681
Yeah.

14:16.856 --> 14:20.294
Marvelous little town.
I've enjoyed my stay.

14:20.468 --> 14:22.035
Are you visiting your family
for the holidays?

14:22.209 --> 14:25.081
No, just a bit of business.

14:25.255 --> 14:27.257
Oh, where are my manners?
Alden Kriss.

14:27.431 --> 14:29.433
Holly.
Holly! Wow.

14:29.607 --> 14:33.916
Aptly named for the holidays.
Yeah, nice to meet you.

14:34.090 --> 14:35.700
I see you've met our
Santa Claus.

14:35.875 --> 14:37.528
Mr. Kriss volunteered to be
the man of the hour...

14:37.702 --> 14:39.313
during the light show.

14:39.487 --> 14:42.055
Well I wish I had known sooner,
before I trimmed my beard.

14:42.751 --> 14:44.579
I think we have a fake one
that came with your costume.

14:44.753 --> 14:46.320
Okay.

14:51.760 --> 14:54.241
Well, I'm looking forward to it,
and nice to meet you.

14:54.415 --> 14:55.677
Very nice to meet you.
Okay.

14:55.851 --> 14:57.679
Thanks, Mr. Kriss.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.204
I didn't think you were
gonna show up.

15:01.378 --> 15:02.771
I keep my promises.

15:04.773 --> 15:05.469
Let's start next door.

15:05.643 --> 15:07.558
Lead the way.

15:19.309 --> 15:21.137
So, the town turned this place
into municipal storage...

15:21.311 --> 15:22.356
a few years ago, we have
everything...

15:22.530 --> 15:24.140
from Terror on the Coast
at Halloween...

15:24.314 --> 15:27.056
sets and props for local
theater.

15:27.230 --> 15:29.667
We did Shakespeare in the park
this summer.

15:29.841 --> 15:30.886
We?

15:31.060 --> 15:34.498
Hamlet needed an understudy.

15:34.672 --> 15:36.544
And how exactly did you end up
in charge of this festival?

15:36.718 --> 15:39.982
I work for the city now,
events coordinator.

15:40.156 --> 15:43.594
Since when?
About a year ago.

15:43.768 --> 15:45.770
You seem surprised.

15:45.945 --> 15:49.644
"It's a big world, Holly. I
can't be tethered to one place."

15:49.818 --> 15:51.254
Are you quoting me now?

15:51.428 --> 15:53.169
Paraphrasing actually.

15:53.343 --> 15:56.825
Yeah, I thought so, I've ever
used the word "tethered", ever.

15:56.999 --> 16:00.785
Okay, here we go. So, this is
our staging area.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.265
It's where volunteers are
working on lights...

16:02.439 --> 16:03.963
and props and signs.

16:04.137 --> 16:06.966
[MIKE] I kind of like to think
of it as Santa's workshop.

16:07.140 --> 16:09.272
Does that make you an elf then?

16:09.446 --> 16:13.450
No, that makes me head elf.

16:13.624 --> 16:15.452
Wow, I don't remember this
festival being quite this...

16:15.626 --> 16:17.715
big before.

16:17.889 --> 16:19.195
Well, it's the first one
in five years...

16:19.369 --> 16:20.675
it's kind of like our grand
return.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.982
The town upped the budget, and
we're pretty lucky...

16:23.156 --> 16:24.984
we had a special benefactor
chip in.

16:25.158 --> 16:27.290
Okay, so, should I just jump in,
make myself useful?

16:29.336 --> 16:31.686
Actually, I have an assignment
just for you.

16:35.864 --> 16:40.216
Okay... what is it?

16:40.390 --> 16:43.828
Nothing... yet, hopefully it's
gonna be a concession stand.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.613
Your mom wants to use it
for her baked goods.

16:45.787 --> 16:47.397
Ought to be a fun project
for you.

16:47.571 --> 16:49.704
Give it the ole Hart touch.

16:49.878 --> 16:51.358
Oh, before I forget.

16:53.012 --> 16:54.883
Yep. Welcome to the team.

16:59.540 --> 17:00.932
Am I supposed to wear this?
Or live inside of it?

17:01.107 --> 17:02.499
It was first come, first serve.

17:02.673 --> 17:04.414
Please tell me these
aren't mandatory.

17:04.588 --> 17:06.677
You're a volunteer, you can
wear it if you like.

17:06.851 --> 17:09.550
The other volunteers are wearing
theirs, so... no pressure.

17:12.031 --> 17:13.423
Okay, here's your tool box--

17:13.597 --> 17:16.905
I think I got it, wood, nails,
I can handle it.

17:17.079 --> 17:19.516
Walking away. Good luck.

17:23.955 --> 17:26.697
Secure legs with screws,
piece of cake.

17:28.873 --> 17:30.353
[ DRILL WHIRRING ]

17:32.225 --> 17:35.445
There should be another
battery in the box.

17:35.619 --> 17:36.533
What?

17:43.192 --> 17:45.934
I was using the drill earlier,
so the battery might be dead.

17:46.108 --> 17:47.762
But there should be an extra.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.329
Oh.

17:52.897 --> 17:55.509
Ah... thanks.

17:58.860 --> 18:00.949
Also... you want to use
a wood screw.

18:01.123 --> 18:02.298
That one's for sheet metal.

18:02.472 --> 18:04.692
You can tell by the thread.
Can I show you?

18:04.866 --> 18:07.608
Sure.

18:12.961 --> 18:14.267
Here.
Thanks.

18:14.441 --> 18:15.964
How'd you get to be such an
expert on this stuff?

18:16.138 --> 18:17.705
My dad taught me.

18:17.879 --> 18:21.143
He says that anything worth
doing, is worth doing right.

18:21.317 --> 18:22.623
Wow, your dad sounds really
smart.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.538
He's the best.

18:26.061 --> 18:27.497
[MIKE]
Hey, Jack?

18:27.671 --> 18:29.673
I gotta go. Right here!

18:32.546 --> 18:34.243
Jack!

18:34.417 --> 18:35.766
[JACK] I'm right here.

18:35.940 --> 18:38.247
What're you doing?

18:40.902 --> 18:42.208
Let's go, bud.

18:59.050 --> 19:01.749
[CAROLINE] Okay, which do you
like better for the front door?

19:01.923 --> 19:03.272
I'd go candy cane.

19:05.883 --> 19:08.843
For the front door?
I've always used solid red.

19:09.017 --> 19:10.845
Why did you ask me then?

19:12.760 --> 19:14.022
I just wanted your opinion.

19:16.851 --> 19:18.592
[ PHONE RINGING ]

19:21.682 --> 19:23.205
Hello?

19:23.379 --> 19:24.641
ASSISTANT [OVER PHONE]
Holly!

19:24.815 --> 19:26.991
I bring tidings of good cheer
and better news.

19:27.166 --> 19:28.254
You're in.

19:28.428 --> 19:30.125
Seriously?

19:30.299 --> 19:32.258
[ASSISTANT] Officially, it's
down to you and two others...

19:32.432 --> 19:34.521
but I've got the inside track
that you're the favorite.

19:34.695 --> 19:36.044
But you didn't hear that
from me.

19:36.218 --> 19:37.741
No, of course not.

19:37.915 --> 19:39.482
ASSISTANT [OVER PHONE]
Sit tight.

19:39.656 --> 19:41.441
Final word won't come
until after the New Year.

19:41.615 --> 19:43.399
But I thought you might
appreciate the heads up.

19:43.573 --> 19:46.228
I do! Thank you so much!
Merry Christmas.

19:46.402 --> 19:47.360
Bye.

19:47.534 --> 19:49.362
Good news?
Very.

19:49.536 --> 19:52.365
I'm up for photo editor at this
really big lifestyle magazine...

19:52.539 --> 19:55.019
in Los Angeles, so I'd have
my own office...

19:55.194 --> 19:57.587
and a staff, and a door
with my name on it.

19:57.761 --> 20:00.286
Oh, honey, that sounds
wonderful.

20:00.460 --> 20:03.811
It is! I mean, there's really
only just one downside...

20:03.985 --> 20:06.509
I, um-- I wouldn't be behind
the camera anymore.

20:08.468 --> 20:11.253
And... you're okay with that?

20:11.427 --> 20:13.168
Well, I mean, I'd still working
with photographs...

20:13.342 --> 20:14.822
it just wouldn't be mine.

20:14.996 --> 20:17.259
I don't know, it just seems like
the next logical step to do...

20:17.433 --> 20:20.001
in my career, and a lot
more money.

20:20.175 --> 20:21.481
Money isn't everything.

20:21.655 --> 20:23.700
Sure is nice, though.

20:23.874 --> 20:26.094
I remember when you were a
little girl growing up...

20:26.268 --> 20:28.401
got your first camera.

20:28.575 --> 20:30.664
You just couldn't put it down.

20:33.188 --> 20:34.450
Well, I'm not a little girl
anymore, Mom.

20:35.973 --> 20:37.714
Yeah, don't remind me.

20:38.149 --> 20:39.020
Love you, mom.

20:44.417 --> 20:47.463
[ CHRISTMAS MUSIC PLAYING ]

21:00.302 --> 21:01.782
There you are.
Morning.

21:01.956 --> 21:04.088
I stopped by Triplett's,
got you a little pick-me-up.

21:04.263 --> 21:06.265
I don't drink coffee.

21:06.439 --> 21:08.397
I know, that's why this is tea.

21:08.571 --> 21:10.486
Two sugars, right?

21:13.359 --> 21:16.362
Yeah... thanks.

21:20.017 --> 21:21.889
I know we didn't end things
on the best of terms...

21:22.063 --> 21:27.503
and I'm partially-- entirely
responsible for that.

21:27.677 --> 21:29.375
So I was hoping
for a little truce?

21:29.549 --> 21:32.203
It's Christmas-time, Peace on
Earth.

21:32.378 --> 21:33.727
Good will towards exes...

21:35.903 --> 21:38.688
Okay... truce.

21:38.862 --> 21:40.168
Truce.

21:45.347 --> 21:49.743
Hey... good to have you back.
Enjoy your tea.

21:58.665 --> 22:01.450
All right, look alive, everyone.
One day closer to show time.

22:10.894 --> 22:13.767
Well, if it isn't the handyman.
Jack, right?

22:15.203 --> 22:16.552
Holly.

22:16.726 --> 22:18.337
Hi, Holly.
Hi, Jack.

22:18.511 --> 22:20.513
How did your stand turn out?

22:20.687 --> 22:24.517
Lopsided... but I think there's
still some time to save it.

22:24.691 --> 22:26.388
Maybe you could give me
a hand later.

22:26.780 --> 22:28.347
Sure.

22:30.261 --> 22:31.437
Did you draw this?

22:31.611 --> 22:33.526
Yep.
Wow.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.702
You're really talented.

22:35.876 --> 22:37.356
You must get that from your dad.

22:37.530 --> 22:40.533
You know my dad?
I do, yeah...

22:40.707 --> 22:42.012
and he's very artistic...

22:42.186 --> 22:44.450
he used to doodle all day
long in his notebooks.

22:44.624 --> 22:46.800
Really?
Yeah.

22:46.974 --> 22:49.411
I've never seen him draw
anything.

22:49.585 --> 22:51.674
He told me I took after my mom.

22:57.637 --> 22:58.725
Hey, you.

22:58.899 --> 23:02.293
Oh, what's all this?

23:02.468 --> 23:04.687
You brought lunch. I figured
I'd bring dessert.

23:06.341 --> 23:08.430
Pecans... candied them myself.

23:08.604 --> 23:12.869
Oh, thank you, Stuart.
These look so delicious.

23:13.043 --> 23:15.132
Don't they?

23:15.306 --> 23:16.873
Oh, sorry.

23:17.047 --> 23:19.398
Here. I'll get the spoon.
Oh, Great.

23:19.572 --> 23:21.617
Okay, here you go.

23:21.791 --> 23:24.272
Here you are, there you go.

23:32.106 --> 23:36.197
[BETTY]
I know! I know! I know...

23:41.855 --> 23:43.639
How excited are you?
I'm so excited.

23:47.251 --> 23:49.123
Oh, I can't wait.

23:51.299 --> 23:52.909
So good.

23:53.083 --> 23:57.087
I, uh... I had a question
for you, Caroline.

23:57.261 --> 23:58.175
Mm-hm.

24:01.265 --> 24:04.660
I was wondering if you'd like
to accompany me...

24:04.834 --> 24:07.750
to the Winter Festival.
Oh.

24:07.924 --> 24:09.839
I know you're running
the concessions and all...

24:10.013 --> 24:12.886
but I thought-- I hoped I could
convince you...

24:13.060 --> 24:15.497
to sneak away to watch
the lights, with me.

24:15.671 --> 24:18.805
Aw... I'm so sorry, Stuart.

24:18.979 --> 24:21.372
I just don't think that's
such a good idea.

24:21.547 --> 24:22.504
You see, I'm just gonna
be so busy--

24:22.678 --> 24:24.463
Of course. No, I understand.

24:24.637 --> 24:27.683
I just thought I'd take a shot.

24:29.293 --> 24:31.861
Hey, do you guys need help
with anything?.

24:32.035 --> 24:34.734
Ah, no, I think she's got
this under control.

24:34.908 --> 24:37.432
You ladies have a great
afternoon.

24:37.606 --> 24:39.173
Same to you.

24:48.443 --> 24:49.923
[HOLLY] Up a little.

24:50.097 --> 24:51.098
[CAROLINE] Here?
[HOLLY] No, to the right.

24:51.272 --> 24:52.926
[CAROLINE] Here?
[HOLLY] Yeah, perfect.

24:53.100 --> 24:54.884
Okay.

24:55.058 --> 24:57.496
Okay, what's next? Tinsel?

24:57.670 --> 25:00.934
That box right behind you.

25:01.108 --> 25:02.457
Okay.

25:05.155 --> 25:07.854
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

25:08.028 --> 25:11.248
New York City. 2006.

25:13.337 --> 25:14.904
My first Christmas being
away from home.

25:15.078 --> 25:17.254
I can't believe you kept
all of these.

25:17.428 --> 25:18.995
Of course, I did.

25:19.169 --> 25:20.997
Even if you were a world away
at Christmas...

25:21.171 --> 25:24.697
it was like having a little
piece of you back home.

25:24.871 --> 25:27.917
I cherished every one
you sent.

25:28.091 --> 25:30.485
Ah, Paris... of course,
I must admit...

25:30.659 --> 25:33.836
I'm not too disappointed
about skipping this year.

25:36.665 --> 25:37.840
Hold that thought.

25:42.410 --> 25:44.847
I figured I could deliver
this one in person.

25:50.505 --> 25:52.333
This maybe my favorite.

25:52.507 --> 25:55.858
Okay, where do I put it?

25:57.207 --> 25:58.469
Right there.

25:58.644 --> 26:00.907
Here? Aw...

26:02.169 --> 26:03.431
Perfect.

26:03.605 --> 26:05.781
I'm so happy you're home.

26:14.181 --> 26:16.792
Eggnog.

26:16.966 --> 26:20.404
Careful, it may have a bit
of a kick.

26:20.579 --> 26:21.623
Oh, really?

26:21.797 --> 26:24.539
Mm-hm, I added extra cinnamon.

26:24.713 --> 26:27.368
You're a wild one, Mom.

26:27.542 --> 26:29.283
Cheers.

26:31.372 --> 26:33.069
You know, this is my favorite
tradition...

26:33.243 --> 26:35.942
after decorating the tree
with your father?

26:36.116 --> 26:37.813
Eggnog on the porch.

26:42.644 --> 26:43.906
Look at him.

26:45.516 --> 26:48.345
He was so handsome
in his dress blues.

26:50.043 --> 26:52.088
You know, he was wearing them
the first night we met?

26:52.262 --> 26:56.919
I laid eyes on him
and I was a goner.

26:57.093 --> 26:59.879
I can't believe it's been
three years.

27:03.534 --> 27:05.928
Mom... have you ever considered
dating again?

27:06.102 --> 27:09.889
Oh, Holly... your father was
the love of my life.

27:10.063 --> 27:12.152
I can't imagine being
with anyone else.

27:12.326 --> 27:18.332
Yeah, I know, but... Dad would
want you to be happy.

27:18.506 --> 27:19.899
I am.

27:25.687 --> 27:28.342
Mr. McGuire seems nice.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.084
Stuart?

27:31.258 --> 27:34.217
You never told me you
guys were so close.

27:34.391 --> 27:37.656
I mean, you know, he makes
weekly deliveries from the farm.

27:37.830 --> 27:41.181
He seems awfully fond of you.

27:41.355 --> 27:46.099
Holly, we're just friends.
I'm just teasing, Mom.

27:46.273 --> 27:49.058
But... if you were more
than that...

27:49.232 --> 27:51.757
you know that'd be okay,
right?

27:56.370 --> 27:57.632
I'm gonna go to bed.

27:59.678 --> 28:02.985
Okay, I'm just gonna spend
a little more time...

28:03.159 --> 28:06.380
with my eggnog...
if you don't mind.

28:09.644 --> 28:12.038
I miss him, too, Mom.

28:14.257 --> 28:15.694
Goodnight.

28:15.868 --> 28:17.086
Goodnight, sweetheart.

28:17.260 --> 28:20.133
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

28:32.798 --> 28:34.190
Well, if I did not know any
better...

28:34.364 --> 28:36.105
I would say that's a concession
stand.

28:36.279 --> 28:38.325
Well, that's what I'm making,
isn't it?

28:38.499 --> 28:40.196
Well, yesterday it was looking
like the Leaning Tower of Pisa.

28:40.370 --> 28:43.330
Yeah, well, I fixed it.

28:43.504 --> 28:46.028
Actually... Jack helped me out.

28:46.202 --> 28:50.119
Makes sense, he's a whiz
at stuff like this.

28:50.293 --> 28:53.775
He's a-- he's a really
great kid.

28:53.949 --> 28:56.647
Thank you, it's all my
influence.

28:56.822 --> 28:58.388
I'm sure.

29:00.695 --> 29:02.479
You know, I am a good guy.

29:02.653 --> 29:06.919
I'm like a ray of sunshine in
the lives of all around me.

29:07.093 --> 29:08.050
In fact, I want to show you
something.

29:08.224 --> 29:09.399
What is it?

29:09.573 --> 29:11.184
You trust me?

29:11.358 --> 29:12.707
No.

29:12.881 --> 29:14.274
Follow me anyway.

29:18.931 --> 29:20.933
Can I get a drum roll?
Want to do a drum roll?

29:21.107 --> 29:23.065
No.
How about a high hat? No? Okay.

29:23.239 --> 29:26.112
Three, two, one, tah-dah.

29:31.900 --> 29:34.773
It's the spitting fish,
we just got done with it.

29:34.947 --> 29:36.687
It's your favorite.

29:39.908 --> 29:41.692
This was your favorite, right?

29:41.867 --> 29:43.346
You remember that?

29:45.479 --> 29:47.263
Of course.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.400
Have you been to Murky Waters
yet?

29:53.574 --> 29:55.184
No, I haven't had a chance yet.

29:55.358 --> 29:59.536
Oh... maybe we should go.

29:59.710 --> 30:01.234
The two of us?

30:01.408 --> 30:04.498
Yeah, my buddy's band is playing
tonight actually.

30:04.672 --> 30:05.978
Like a date?

30:06.152 --> 30:07.414
I meant to be strictly
platonic...

30:07.588 --> 30:10.156
but if your heart is set
on a date, you can twist my arm.

30:10.330 --> 30:12.114
Are you seriously asking me
out right now?

30:12.288 --> 30:15.161
Okay, are you with someone?

30:15.335 --> 30:17.293
Am I with someone?

30:17.467 --> 30:21.384
Okay... not interested, can't
blame a guy for trying.

30:21.558 --> 30:24.213
You know what? Everyone told me
to give you a chance.

30:24.387 --> 30:28.348
Try to be friends, but this
is a new low, even for you.

30:28.522 --> 30:30.045
Find a new volunteer.

30:38.358 --> 30:40.229
Holly!

30:40.403 --> 30:42.057
You remember Betty Escher...

30:42.231 --> 30:43.667
she was a few years behind
you in school.

30:43.842 --> 30:46.496
I think the last time
you saw me, I was in braces.

30:46.670 --> 30:48.629
No! Yeah! Uh, of course,
I remember you.

30:48.803 --> 30:50.544
Sorry, I didn't mean
to interrupt.

30:50.718 --> 30:53.460
I was just going to my room
to grab my camera.

30:53.634 --> 30:55.984
Oh, no! Come sit down!
You're not interrupting at all.

30:56.158 --> 30:57.333
I'll pour you some tea.

30:57.507 --> 30:59.596
Betty's helping with the
concession stand.

30:59.770 --> 31:02.077
We were going to finalize
the menu...

31:02.251 --> 31:06.212
but kind of got sidetracked
with the wedding planning.

31:06.386 --> 31:07.300
Wedding planning?

31:10.651 --> 31:12.044
You're engaged.

31:12.218 --> 31:15.177
As of a two nights ago,
he proposed at the park.

31:15.351 --> 31:17.049
When they were testing
out some of the lights.

31:17.223 --> 31:20.530
Drops down to his knee right in
front of the shooting stars.

31:20.704 --> 31:22.271
Isn't that just the most
romantic thing...

31:22.445 --> 31:24.360
you've ever heard?

31:24.534 --> 31:24.970
Yeah.

31:26.928 --> 31:29.061
I'm hoping to convince your mom
to cater for me.

31:29.235 --> 31:31.193
Oh, Betty, it's your big day.

31:31.367 --> 31:32.891
You should have a professional
handle all that.

31:33.065 --> 31:34.370
Holly, please tell your momma...

31:34.544 --> 31:36.198
that no one makes a better
peach cobbler.

31:37.852 --> 31:39.158
Holly could take pictures!

31:39.332 --> 31:40.463
Could you, Holly?

31:40.637 --> 31:43.075
I, uh--
Of course, she could.

31:43.249 --> 31:45.338
You are the best!

31:45.512 --> 31:47.862
Oh, I'm just the luckiest girl
in the whole world!

31:48.036 --> 31:50.212
Oh, you're precious.

31:54.782 --> 31:56.958
Betty? Hey, hold up a second.

31:57.132 --> 31:58.568
What is it?

31:58.742 --> 32:03.443
Uh... I can't-- I can't
go to your wedding.

32:03.747 --> 32:08.187
Oh, well, that's okay, I know we
kinda put you on the spot.

32:08.361 --> 32:10.232
No, I mean, I can't go
because...

32:12.278 --> 32:14.410
your fiancé made a pass at me.

32:14.584 --> 32:16.456
What?

32:16.630 --> 32:18.414
I-- I'm sorry, I didn't know
if I should say anything.

32:18.588 --> 32:21.461
But I just didn't feel right
keeping it from you.

32:21.635 --> 32:24.725
Um, when did this happen?

32:24.899 --> 32:27.554
Today... at the park.

32:27.728 --> 32:30.252
Maybe he was just being
friendly?

32:30.426 --> 32:32.167
He's a real friendly guy.

32:34.778 --> 32:36.171
He asked me out on a date.

32:37.956 --> 32:40.219
Oh.
I'm sorry.

32:40.393 --> 32:42.482
I don't know, I mean, maybe
he just, uh...

32:42.656 --> 32:44.223
got caught up in the moment.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.965
I mean, we do have a past
together, so--

32:47.139 --> 32:51.317
A past? You dated Benny?

32:53.493 --> 32:55.103
Benny?

32:55.277 --> 32:57.584
Aren't you engaged to Mike?

32:57.758 --> 33:00.543
Wha-- Mike? No!

33:00.717 --> 33:02.719
He's like a brother to me.

33:02.893 --> 33:06.288
But I saw you two yesterday,
he was spinning you around...

33:06.462 --> 33:07.550
and you guys were hugging.

33:07.724 --> 33:09.552
I was letting him know
Benny proposed.

33:09.726 --> 33:12.338
He's the one who introduced us.

33:12.512 --> 33:14.383
Then who is Jack?

33:14.557 --> 33:17.256
That's Mike's nephew,
Steve's little boy.

33:17.430 --> 33:21.564
Oh, Holly, you gave me
quite a scare.

33:21.738 --> 33:25.481
Oh, and just so you know...
Mike's as single as they come.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.440
If you need a
date for the wedding.

33:29.616 --> 33:30.660
Huh.

33:32.662 --> 33:34.360
Oh, crap.

33:41.497 --> 33:43.369
Okay. These need to be taken
outside.

33:44.109 --> 33:44.979
Yeah, that's the right box.

33:45.153 --> 33:46.241
Thank you.

33:54.249 --> 33:56.817
Good morning.
Hi.

33:56.991 --> 33:59.994
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

34:03.606 --> 34:05.434
What's that?

34:05.608 --> 34:08.524
Uh... an apology...

34:08.698 --> 34:12.050
And sticky buns, apology
sticky buns.

34:16.706 --> 34:20.928
Hm... I didn't think you were
coming back.

34:21.102 --> 34:23.713
Yeah, about that, I, uh...

34:23.887 --> 34:27.456
I may have assumed you had
a wife and child.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.110
What?

34:29.284 --> 34:34.898
Look, I misread the situation,
and I'm really sorry.

34:35.073 --> 34:38.989
Well, makes me feel a little bit
better about the rejection.

34:41.905 --> 34:42.689
You want to start over?

34:42.863 --> 34:44.299
Can we?

34:47.781 --> 34:48.608
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

34:54.179 --> 34:56.485
Holly?

34:56.659 --> 35:01.055
Holly? I didn't know
you were in town.

35:01.229 --> 35:02.404
I didn't tell you.

35:02.578 --> 35:04.754
Oh, of course, you can have
my number.

35:04.928 --> 35:06.495
Don't beg, it's embarrassing,
there's people around.

35:06.669 --> 35:07.670
That's not how that happened.

35:07.844 --> 35:09.411
It's how I remember it.

35:13.241 --> 35:16.505
Okay, you're what, a day
behind on your project?

35:16.679 --> 35:18.855
You need some help?

35:19.029 --> 35:20.422
That would be great.

35:23.338 --> 35:25.340
Ooh, nice shirt, by the way.

35:30.563 --> 35:32.652
I've been to Russia, France,
Brazil...

35:32.826 --> 35:35.263
and last year I spent
Christmas in Ukraine.

35:35.437 --> 35:37.439
Wow.
Yeah.

35:37.613 --> 35:39.311
Do you know, they don't decorate
their trees with tinsel?

35:39.485 --> 35:41.313
They use spider webs.

35:41.487 --> 35:43.967
Cool!
Right?

35:44.142 --> 35:45.360
Hey, Holly?
Yeah?

35:45.534 --> 35:46.622
Do you like mac and cheese?

35:46.796 --> 35:48.146
Yeah, why?

35:48.320 --> 35:49.973
Hey, Uncle Mike?
Yeah.

35:50.148 --> 35:52.585
Can Holly come over for mac
and cheese tonight?

35:54.369 --> 35:58.417
You should.
Okay, I'll be there.

35:58.591 --> 36:00.070
Excuse me.

36:00.245 --> 36:03.552
Hey, Mike, you know
where the ladder is?

36:03.726 --> 36:06.512
Yes, it's on Billy's truck,
and he's at lunch.

36:06.686 --> 36:09.602
There's a light out
on the shooting star...

36:09.776 --> 36:10.559
and the bulbs are all the way
at the top.

36:10.733 --> 36:12.692
I can't climb that high.

36:12.866 --> 36:15.260
Who needs a ladder? Let's show
'em how it's done, bud.

36:19.916 --> 36:21.483
Those two are pretty close, huh?

36:21.657 --> 36:25.531
Oh, yeah... Steve's real lucky
it worked out the way it did.

36:25.705 --> 36:27.359
What do you mean?

36:27.533 --> 36:29.578
He's overseas, you didn't
know that?

36:29.752 --> 36:32.842
No.
Well, he's in the Army.

36:33.016 --> 36:35.410
Mike's looking after Jack
while he's deployed.

36:35.584 --> 36:36.890
What happened to Jack's mother?

36:37.064 --> 36:39.762
She was in the service, too.
Heck, that's how they met.

36:39.936 --> 36:42.983
She passed a few years ago.

36:43.157 --> 36:45.028
[HOLLY] That's awful.

36:45.203 --> 36:47.422
Mike had a life out
in Nashville...

36:47.596 --> 36:51.600
but he dropped it all to come
back here and look after Jack.

36:51.774 --> 36:54.734
That's what family does...
that's a good man.

36:56.126 --> 36:58.738
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

37:04.831 --> 37:06.224
Oh, wow!

37:06.398 --> 37:09.401
Betty, these look so good!

37:09.575 --> 37:11.838
Really? You're not just sparing
my feelings, right?

37:12.012 --> 37:13.361
Have Holly try.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.450
I never spare feelings.

37:17.974 --> 37:20.107
Mm, mm-hm, yeah.

37:20.281 --> 37:21.717
See?

37:21.891 --> 37:23.589
Oh, by the way, Betty and Benny
have invited...

37:23.763 --> 37:24.720
us to dinner tonight.

37:24.894 --> 37:26.418
If you're not busy.

37:26.592 --> 37:28.333
Actually, um, can I have a rain
check? I have plans.

37:28.507 --> 37:30.596
Plans?

37:30.770 --> 37:32.598
Yeah, I'm going to Mike's.

37:32.772 --> 37:35.601
It's not like that.

37:35.775 --> 37:36.950
I did not say a thing.

37:37.124 --> 37:39.518
Uh, she didn't, but I will.
I love this!

37:39.692 --> 37:41.259
It's just dinner.

37:41.433 --> 37:43.609
But dinner can lead to more.

37:43.783 --> 37:45.654
We tried more, that--
that did not work out.

37:45.828 --> 37:47.526
Well, what happened?

37:47.700 --> 37:50.093
It's a long story.

37:50.268 --> 37:52.879
Well, I don't have anywhere
to be. Do you, Caroline?

37:53.053 --> 37:54.707
No, I live here.

37:58.101 --> 38:01.409
Okay, um, we graduated
high school...

38:01.583 --> 38:04.717
and I went off to college.

38:04.891 --> 38:06.849
Holly was at the top
of her class.

38:07.023 --> 38:08.590
Would you like to tell this?

38:08.764 --> 38:10.810
Sorry.. continue.

38:10.984 --> 38:12.464
Mike decided that he was gonna
take a year off...

38:12.638 --> 38:14.857
and then follow me.

38:15.031 --> 38:19.384
Except, when it was time to go,
he changed his mind.

38:19.558 --> 38:20.863
Oh.

38:21.037 --> 38:22.517
Said he didn't know what
he wanted...

38:22.691 --> 38:24.780
and that he needed to go
out and find it.

38:24.954 --> 38:28.523
And, apparently, that didn't
include me.

38:30.612 --> 38:32.571
Well, you're both here.

38:32.745 --> 38:35.530
Maybe this is your second
chance.

38:41.493 --> 38:44.539
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

38:56.334 --> 38:58.640
You're here!
I'm here.

39:02.340 --> 39:03.645
Follow me! I want to show
you something in my room!

39:03.819 --> 39:05.386
Okay.

39:05.560 --> 39:07.736
Whoa.

39:07.910 --> 39:09.521
He's excited that you're here.

39:09.695 --> 39:11.566
[JACK]
Come on, Holly!

39:14.177 --> 39:15.657
Hi.
Hi.

39:17.267 --> 39:18.791
[JACK]
These are fighter planes...

39:18.965 --> 39:20.880
this one's a Mustang and this
one's a Tomcat.

39:21.054 --> 39:23.970
[JACK] I also have a few bombers
and some Army tanks...

39:24.144 --> 39:25.754
I'm trying to grow my
collection.

39:25.928 --> 39:27.626
[HOLLY] Wow, did you build
all these?

39:27.800 --> 39:29.671
With my dad.

39:29.845 --> 39:32.805
You know, my dad used to fly
in one of these.

39:32.979 --> 39:34.284
Really?

39:34.459 --> 39:36.069
Yeah, he was in the Air Force.

39:36.243 --> 39:38.637
He was stationed
at Keesler Airbase.

39:38.811 --> 39:40.987
It's not far from here.
That's cool.

39:41.161 --> 39:42.684
Yeah.

39:44.425 --> 39:46.862
This is what I'm working on now.
It's Santa's sleigh.

39:47.036 --> 39:49.561
I'm gonna surprise my dad
for Christmas.

39:49.735 --> 39:52.868
Ssh, you can't tell.
Scout's honor.

40:08.362 --> 40:11.626
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

40:24.160 --> 40:25.335
So, the cob webs were
in the same box...

40:25.510 --> 40:27.120
as the Halloween decorations.

40:27.294 --> 40:29.862
Yeah, not exactly how they
do it in Ukraine...

40:30.036 --> 40:32.734
but I like whatever's
happening here.

40:32.908 --> 40:35.694
If you'll follow me,
dinner is ready.

40:47.140 --> 40:48.794
You kept this?

40:51.797 --> 40:54.713
Yeah, it was a gift.

40:59.369 --> 41:00.675
Food's getting cold.

41:08.683 --> 41:10.424
You remember the time we went
swimming after church...

41:10.598 --> 41:11.686
down behind McGuire's farm?

41:11.860 --> 41:14.950
Oh, my gosh, what were we,
nine, ten?

41:15.124 --> 41:17.431
Ten... yeah, remember you
rode on my bike...

41:17.605 --> 41:18.737
that I got for my birthday.

41:18.911 --> 41:22.044
Yeah, the one with the wobbly
handlebars.

41:22.218 --> 41:24.046
They were not wobbly,
you didn't sit on them right.

41:24.220 --> 41:25.657
Because they were wobbling.

41:25.831 --> 41:26.962
You wouldn't sit still.

41:27.136 --> 41:30.052
They weren't wobbly.
Yes, they were.

41:30.226 --> 41:33.882
My mama was furious. She'd just
bought me that new dress...

41:34.056 --> 41:36.450
and there I was,
splashing in the creek.

41:38.974 --> 41:42.500
So... you guys used to be
friends?

41:42.674 --> 41:46.025
Yeah... yeah, we were.

41:50.812 --> 41:52.422
Cool.

41:56.470 --> 42:00.213
Okay... okay... oh!

42:00.387 --> 42:03.695
[HOLLY] Yes! Holly is amazing!
That's a goal!

42:03.869 --> 42:06.436
[JACK] Let's go again,
best two out of three.

42:11.659 --> 42:14.053
[ PHONE RINGS ]

42:14.227 --> 42:15.750
Hello?

42:17.360 --> 42:18.231
Hey, little brother.

42:18.405 --> 42:20.581
Hey, man! Got your bags packed?

42:20.755 --> 42:23.149
Yeah, look, look, about that.

42:23.323 --> 42:26.544
STEVE [OVER PHONE]
Something's come up.

42:26.718 --> 42:28.850
[HOLLY] Come on, Jack, you
got this. Go for it!

42:29.329 --> 42:31.200
He scores!

42:35.335 --> 42:37.816
Jack, your dad's on the phone.

42:44.562 --> 42:47.129
Dad, guess what! We almost have
the whole light show set up!

42:47.303 --> 42:50.568
I helped with the banner and
Holly-- wait, do you know Holly?

42:50.742 --> 42:52.570
Holly said I draw really well.

42:52.744 --> 42:55.573
Is everything okay?

42:55.747 --> 42:58.793
Steve's stuck at the base.

42:58.967 --> 43:00.926
Storms are rolling in and
they're grounding flights...

43:01.100 --> 43:02.710
for the next few days.

43:02.884 --> 43:05.234
Oh, no.

43:05.408 --> 43:07.976
He's trying to make arrangements
when they settle down, but--

43:08.150 --> 43:11.893
He's gonna miss Christmas.

43:18.683 --> 43:21.076
Jack! Jack.

43:21.250 --> 43:22.817
Hey, Jack!

43:29.389 --> 43:32.305
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
Jack, I'm really sorry.

43:32.479 --> 43:34.133
I know how much you were looking
forward to your dad...

43:34.307 --> 43:36.788
coming home for Christmas.

43:36.962 --> 43:39.529
[MIKE] Look, bud, it's only
gonna be a few more days.

43:39.704 --> 43:42.924
[MIKE] We can have our own
celebration when he gets home.

43:45.231 --> 43:47.886
[MIKE] Come on, Jack, will you
open the door for me?

43:50.758 --> 43:53.108
Can I try?

43:54.283 --> 43:55.850
Yeah.

43:59.419 --> 44:03.597
Hey, Jack? It's Holly,
can we talk?

44:05.904 --> 44:07.906
[ STEPS APPROACHING ]

44:08.080 --> 44:09.995
[ LOCK CLICKS OPENS ]

44:16.001 --> 44:19.004
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

44:25.532 --> 44:28.404
Thanks for letting me come in.

44:28.578 --> 44:32.452
I know how hard it can be to
keep saying goodbye to your dad.

44:32.626 --> 44:35.063
I had to do that a lot
growing up.

44:35.237 --> 44:37.065
Did your dad ever miss
Christmas?

44:37.239 --> 44:40.025
A couple of them, yeah.

44:41.635 --> 44:44.986
Really? What did you do?

44:51.689 --> 44:53.212
Can I show you something?

44:59.435 --> 45:01.394
One Christmas, just before he
was scheduled to be deployed...

45:01.568 --> 45:05.964
again, my dad took me outside,
he told me to choose a star.

45:06.138 --> 45:07.879
He said that whenever
I missed him...

45:08.053 --> 45:11.665
I should look up at that star,
and he'd do the same.

45:15.495 --> 45:17.192
We picked that one.

45:24.852 --> 45:27.246
The world's a big place, but
knowing that he was looking...

45:27.420 --> 45:31.685
at the same star, suddenly he
didn't seem so far away.

45:34.340 --> 45:36.951
Maybe when my dad gets back,
we can do the same thing.

45:39.127 --> 45:40.650
I think that'd be a really
good idea.

45:40.825 --> 45:42.087
Come here.

46:04.892 --> 46:08.069
Sorry, Dasher. No luck yet.

46:22.605 --> 46:24.912
Oh good, you're up!

46:25.086 --> 46:26.479
Good morning!

46:26.653 --> 46:30.744
Hi. What are you doing here
so early?

46:30.918 --> 46:33.312
You up for a field trip?

46:36.794 --> 46:39.318
[ WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ]

46:47.543 --> 46:49.284
[HOLLY] Wow, when did they build
this place?

46:49.458 --> 46:52.070
About four years ago,
after the hurricane...

46:52.244 --> 46:54.333
this town was in really
rough shape.

46:54.507 --> 46:57.031
A lot of businesses
were forced to shut down.

46:57.205 --> 46:58.990
They didn't want to,
of course...

46:59.164 --> 47:01.514
but the insurance money
doesn't cover everything.

47:01.688 --> 47:05.257
When the businesses go,
the people aren't far behind.

47:05.431 --> 47:08.129
They built this resort,
created a lot of jobs...

47:08.303 --> 47:10.001
and really helped Gulfport
bounce back.

47:10.175 --> 47:11.567
And in a stroke of good luck...

47:11.741 --> 47:14.048
the developer was gonna build
this in New Orleans...

47:14.222 --> 47:17.095
but at the very last minute,
moved construction to here.

47:17.269 --> 47:19.358
Excuse me, we're picking up
the lights for the festival.

47:19.532 --> 47:21.229
Could you help us out?
Point us in the right direction?

47:21.403 --> 47:23.449
Oh, yeah, of course, follow me.

47:23.623 --> 47:26.278
So when Island View found out
that the city was gonna...

47:26.452 --> 47:28.149
resurrect the light show...

47:28.323 --> 47:29.977
they not only gave us
a big donation...

47:30.151 --> 47:32.153
they gave us all of their
lights.

47:33.589 --> 47:35.026
We are coming to collect.

47:35.200 --> 47:37.811
All right, here we are.

47:41.467 --> 47:42.511
Whoa.

47:42.685 --> 47:44.165
Go check it out.

47:46.646 --> 47:49.127
Wait a minute... so this
is my surprise?

47:49.301 --> 47:51.042
Helping you carry cardboard
boxes?

47:51.216 --> 47:55.350
No, this is your surprise.

47:59.224 --> 48:01.791
Is that...?
Ship Island? Yup.

48:03.924 --> 48:05.099
Best view of it in the city.

48:07.841 --> 48:09.408
Holly's dad used to take us
fishing there.

48:09.582 --> 48:11.714
Yeah, and every Christmas,
we'd go hunt for oysters.

48:11.889 --> 48:14.587
Yeah, we'd spend all morning
out on that skiff.

48:14.761 --> 48:18.199
He said other than home,
it's his favorite place to be.

48:18.373 --> 48:20.375
Can I see?
Yeah.

48:20.549 --> 48:22.464
Here, I'll set it up
for you again.

48:22.638 --> 48:25.250
Yeah, it's right there.

48:27.513 --> 48:29.819
Wow.

48:32.083 --> 48:35.303
Hey, Jack, take this quarter...

48:35.477 --> 48:37.001
and go-- go check out the view
from over there.

48:37.175 --> 48:39.133
Okay, thank you.

48:41.614 --> 48:44.443
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

48:46.314 --> 48:48.969
Thank you... for taking
me here.

48:49.143 --> 48:51.276
Thought you might like it.

48:53.756 --> 48:56.890
You know, sometimes I wonder
if he'd be proud of me.

48:58.718 --> 49:00.372
Of course, he would.

49:00.546 --> 49:02.678
He dedicated his life
to something.

49:02.852 --> 49:04.811
What have I ever done?

49:04.985 --> 49:10.469
You show people things they've
never seen before.

49:10.643 --> 49:12.427
I find that important.

49:14.038 --> 49:15.256
Maybe.

49:18.825 --> 49:22.176
Do you have time for one
more stop?

49:24.787 --> 49:27.877
[ MUSIC PLAYING ]

49:38.149 --> 49:39.541
Uncle Mike!
Yep.

49:39.715 --> 49:42.501
Can I go see Benny?
Yeah.

49:46.592 --> 49:47.462
What's up, man?

49:47.636 --> 49:49.073
[HOLLY] How's he doing?

49:49.247 --> 49:51.640
He's put on a brave face,
but he's disappointed.

49:51.814 --> 49:52.902
Yeah, well, we'll just have
to give him...

49:53.077 --> 49:54.426
the best Christmas ever, then.

49:56.210 --> 49:58.473
We?

49:58.647 --> 50:01.302
Yeah, we.

50:06.177 --> 50:08.309
Triplett's has my photos up?

50:09.789 --> 50:12.139
Yeah, that's why I took
you here.

50:12.313 --> 50:14.446
A lot of places do.

50:14.620 --> 50:16.230
Why?

50:18.580 --> 50:23.324
A reminder... that there's
a lot of good in this world.

50:25.979 --> 50:28.329
When I look at these photos,
I don't see flooded streets.

50:28.503 --> 50:31.550
I don't see broken glass.

50:31.724 --> 50:33.552
I see the volunteers who handed
out drinking water.

50:35.989 --> 50:38.426
I see fishermen spending hours
on skiffs...

50:38.600 --> 50:40.559
searching for people stranded
on their roofs.

50:43.953 --> 50:46.260
I see friends, I see family.

50:48.045 --> 50:51.396
I see strangers...
I see neighbors.

50:53.615 --> 50:55.269
All coming together looking
to help.

50:58.838 --> 51:01.014
Your pictures, they mean
something to this town.

51:03.712 --> 51:05.584
So do you.

51:14.071 --> 51:15.594
Well, come on! Let us see it!

51:15.768 --> 51:18.292
[MR. KRISS] Well, it's a little
big in the belly!

51:26.213 --> 51:28.085
I think it looks great.

51:28.259 --> 51:30.217
Though you may need some
extra padding to fill it out.

51:30.391 --> 51:32.698
There was a time that this would
have fit me perfectly.

51:32.872 --> 51:36.180
My wife convinced me
to skip the cookies.

51:36.354 --> 51:38.965
There... now you look
like Santa.

51:39.139 --> 51:40.314
Oh...

51:42.925 --> 51:46.451
All right, the look's great, but
we'd have to hear the vocals.

51:48.757 --> 51:50.542
Ho! Ho! Ho!

51:52.413 --> 51:54.241
No, no, wait, wait.

51:54.415 --> 51:56.374
Ho, ho, ho! No, no--

51:58.071 --> 52:00.334
It should be deeper,
so your stomach shakes...

52:00.508 --> 52:02.249
like a bowl full of jelly.

52:02.423 --> 52:05.861
A bowlful of jelly?

52:06.035 --> 52:07.907
Hoo-hoo-hoo.

52:09.778 --> 52:11.476
Ho-ho-ho.

52:14.087 --> 52:16.089
All right, I'll work on it.

52:16.263 --> 52:18.439
This is so itchy.

52:26.621 --> 52:28.145
Hey.
Hey.

52:33.585 --> 52:34.412
Can I help you with something?

52:34.586 --> 52:36.501
Yes... information.

52:36.675 --> 52:38.633
Oh, I don't know much
about the whole operation.

52:38.807 --> 52:40.766
I just make the stand,
but I think I saw Benny--

52:40.940 --> 52:43.290
Not about the festival...
about you and Mike!

52:43.464 --> 52:46.075
There is no me and Mike.

52:46.250 --> 52:48.469
So you didn't ride
in together today?

52:48.643 --> 52:50.602
Well, no, we did--

52:50.776 --> 52:52.299
And you weren't at his house
until almost 10:00 o'clock...

52:52.473 --> 52:53.344
the other night?

52:53.518 --> 52:54.867
What are you a lawyer?

52:55.041 --> 52:57.304
Actually, I am, but right now,
I'm just being nosy.

52:59.176 --> 53:01.221
Oh... well, in that case,
I plead the fifth.

53:01.395 --> 53:02.701
Come on.

53:02.875 --> 53:04.485
There's nothing to tell.
I've been back for six days.

53:04.659 --> 53:07.184
But you and Mike dated
for four years.

53:07.358 --> 53:09.577
Yeah, but I haven't seen him
in like, almost ten years.

53:09.751 --> 53:12.363
Ugh, I can't wait that long.

53:12.537 --> 53:14.582
You're really invested
in this.

53:14.756 --> 53:17.498
I love Mike, everyone does!

53:17.672 --> 53:19.370
When he was put in charge
of the festival...

53:19.544 --> 53:22.460
the whole town lined up
to help out.

53:22.634 --> 53:25.202
Incidentally, I was really happy
to be teamed up with your mom...

53:25.376 --> 53:26.551
and the concession stand.

53:26.725 --> 53:31.164
She has the best gossip in town.
Yeah, it's true.

53:31.338 --> 53:33.688
Mike's one of my absolute
favorite people.

53:33.862 --> 53:37.126
And if anyone deserves
happiness, it's him.

53:37.301 --> 53:38.693
Yeah, I want that for him,
too...

53:38.867 --> 53:42.219
but this is just two friends
catching up, that's all.

53:42.393 --> 53:44.221
Does he know that?

53:46.440 --> 53:48.616
All right.
Come on, let's go!

53:48.790 --> 53:50.705
I can beat you, I'll beat you.

53:56.363 --> 53:59.366
[ SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES ]

54:07.026 --> 54:08.897
All right, you guys ready
to light up Mr. Kriss...

54:09.071 --> 54:11.465
a.k.a. Malibu Santa?

54:11.639 --> 54:13.380
Ready!
All right, three, two--

54:20.735 --> 54:22.563
They're not on.

54:22.737 --> 54:27.089
Okay... uh, don't tell Benny
I was touching this.

54:27.264 --> 54:30.136
Okay, I'll figure it out,
give me a second.

54:32.747 --> 54:34.488
Well, we're getting close
to Christmas.

54:34.662 --> 54:37.622
Are you excited?
I guess.

54:37.796 --> 54:39.841
You guess?

54:40.015 --> 54:45.456
My dad was supposed to come home
for Christmas... but he's stuck.

54:45.630 --> 54:48.154
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

54:48.328 --> 54:51.984
Well, maybe-- maybe
he could get unstuck.

54:53.551 --> 54:55.640
Do you really think that
could happen?

54:55.814 --> 55:00.601
You know, Jack, I've learned to
never count out a miracle...

55:00.775 --> 55:02.299
especially at Christmas.

55:08.130 --> 55:09.393
Whoa!

55:09.567 --> 55:12.309
I got it!

55:17.139 --> 55:19.490
Thanks for the ride.
Anytime.

55:19.664 --> 55:21.318
Bye, Jack.
Bye.

55:28.237 --> 55:30.501
Hey, Holly?
Yeah?

55:30.675 --> 55:32.459
Are you doing anything later?

55:32.633 --> 55:35.114
I don't think so.

55:35.288 --> 55:37.638
Do you want to maybe...
grab some dinner?

55:37.812 --> 55:39.510
Sure.

55:39.684 --> 55:42.034
Great! It's a date.

55:49.737 --> 55:52.653
[ MUSIC PLAYING ]

55:52.827 --> 55:55.439
♪ Deck the halls with boughs
of holly ♪

55:55.613 --> 55:58.267
♪ Fa la la la la
la la la la ♪

55:58.442 --> 56:00.748
♪ Tis the season to be jolly

56:00.922 --> 56:03.403
♪ Fa la la la la
la la la la ♪

56:03.577 --> 56:05.753
♪ Don we now our gay apparel

56:05.927 --> 56:09.104
♪ Fa la la la la
la la la la ♪

56:10.715 --> 56:12.717
♪ Troll the ancient
Yuletide carol ♪

56:12.891 --> 56:15.459
♪ Fa la la la la
la la la la ♪

56:15.633 --> 56:18.505
♪ Fa la la la la
la la la la ♪

56:18.679 --> 56:20.115
Sure you don't mind
watching Jack tonight?

56:20.289 --> 56:22.161
Oh, of course not!
Okay.

56:22.335 --> 56:23.771
This little boy is a dream.

56:23.945 --> 56:26.034
Careful, that goes to his head.

56:26.208 --> 56:27.862
I heard that.

56:28.036 --> 56:31.605
Hey, what are you two doing
tomorrow night?

56:31.779 --> 56:33.825
Since we'll all be working
the light show...

56:33.999 --> 56:35.827
Christmas Eve, I'm having
a little "Christmas Eve Eve"...

56:36.001 --> 56:38.264
dinner here at the house.

56:38.438 --> 56:39.700
You know, we had the same
thought.

56:39.874 --> 56:41.963
I was gonna attempt a turkey.

56:42.137 --> 56:44.618
We bought a fire extinguisher
last week, just in case.

56:44.792 --> 56:47.795
Jack... bro code, dude.

56:47.969 --> 56:50.711
You two have to come here!
It's just gonna be Holly and me.

56:50.885 --> 56:52.583
And Lord knows, I'll have too
much food.

56:52.757 --> 56:54.411
[HOLLY] She will.

57:08.686 --> 57:09.556
You should come.

57:11.079 --> 57:12.429
Sounds good.

57:16.694 --> 57:18.478
You look beautiful.
Thanks.

57:22.177 --> 57:24.484
Uh, Caroline. I promise to have
her back before curfew.

57:27.182 --> 57:28.488
After you.

57:28.662 --> 57:31.056
Bye, Momma.
[CAROLINE] Bye.

57:31.230 --> 57:32.536
Have fun.

57:38.193 --> 57:40.108
So, Jack, do you like
gingerbread?

57:40.282 --> 57:41.719
Yeah.

57:41.893 --> 57:44.852
Boy, do I have a surprise
for you.

57:45.026 --> 57:47.812
Ms. Caroline?
Yes, Jack?

57:47.986 --> 57:50.858
Do you believe in miracles?
I do.

57:51.032 --> 57:53.470
So... it's not silly to wish
for them?

57:59.258 --> 58:02.391
Things may not always turn out
the way you want them to, Jack.

58:02.566 --> 58:05.873
But there's nothing silly
about having faith...

58:06.047 --> 58:07.527
that hard times are gonna
get better.

58:10.356 --> 58:12.489
Now how about some icing?

58:20.888 --> 58:23.804
Here we are. I found it!

58:23.978 --> 58:26.546
I was hoping you could help me
with something.

58:26.720 --> 58:29.114
It's kind of a... secret
mission.

58:29.288 --> 58:30.637
What is it?

58:30.811 --> 58:33.292
Open it and see.

58:33.466 --> 58:35.686
Some have chimneys, but all
have locks...

58:35.860 --> 58:38.253
the key to entry is in this box.

58:45.739 --> 58:47.611
It's a key.
A master key.

58:47.785 --> 58:49.700
What does it open?

58:49.874 --> 58:52.050
Every house in Gulfport.

58:52.224 --> 58:55.444
In the South, not many houses
have chimneys.

58:55.619 --> 58:59.144
So how is Santa supposed
to deliver all of his toys?

58:59.318 --> 59:01.015
With this?

59:01.189 --> 59:04.671
It was given to my family many
years ago for safe keeping.

59:04.845 --> 59:07.848
Holly used to be in charge of
it, but now that she's older...

59:08.022 --> 59:11.156
I was hoping you
could take the job.

59:11.330 --> 59:12.853
What do I do?

59:13.027 --> 59:16.901
When you get home, put
the key in your mailbox.

59:17.075 --> 59:19.773
Santa will take it and use it
on Christmas Eve.

59:19.947 --> 59:21.949
When Santa's finished...

59:22.123 --> 59:24.735
he'll find a way to get
it back to you.

59:24.909 --> 59:26.998
So what do you think?

59:27.172 --> 59:31.219
I'll do it. You can count on me.

59:31.393 --> 59:33.570
I knew I could.

59:42.709 --> 59:43.710
Got it.

59:43.884 --> 59:45.886
Got what?

59:46.060 --> 59:47.496
Are you taking pictures of me?

59:47.671 --> 59:49.063
I wanted a spontaneous photo.

59:49.237 --> 59:50.935
Of the back of my head?
That's not my good side.

59:51.109 --> 59:53.590
Okay, fine, then strike a pose.
That's my good side.

59:57.681 --> 59:58.986
Got it.

59:59.160 --> 1:00:00.684
Let me see it. No, yeah,
I don't want to see it.

1:00:00.858 --> 1:00:01.902
No.

1:00:02.076 --> 1:00:03.730
All right, where to next?

1:00:03.904 --> 1:00:05.732
I don't know, it's getting
late...

1:00:05.906 --> 1:00:06.907
so maybe we should just
head back.

1:00:07.081 --> 1:00:08.996
It's 9:00, city girl.

1:00:09.170 --> 1:00:11.869
Okay, well then,
what do you suggest?

1:00:12.043 --> 1:00:13.827
Dessert.

1:00:14.001 --> 1:00:15.960
Okay.

1:00:16.134 --> 1:00:19.833
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:00:20.007 --> 1:00:24.838
It was nice of Benny to give you
the keys to this place.

1:00:25.012 --> 1:00:26.840
He owes me a favor.

1:00:27.014 --> 1:00:28.886
Okay, you ready?
Yes.

1:00:29.060 --> 1:00:32.629
We have strawberry, chocolate,
vanilla.

1:00:34.326 --> 1:00:36.763
D... all of the above.

1:00:36.937 --> 1:00:39.331
Stop. Good answer.

1:00:41.986 --> 1:00:43.988
You know, most people
only get two scoops.

1:00:44.162 --> 1:00:46.686
I've always made yours
with three.

1:00:46.860 --> 1:00:49.428
Well, no wonder I fell for you.

1:00:51.299 --> 1:00:52.561
Three.

1:00:54.041 --> 1:00:56.435
[ BLENDER WHIRRING ]

1:01:19.110 --> 1:01:22.548
You've still got it.
Thank you, thank you very much.

1:01:22.722 --> 1:01:25.029
I've had some practice.

1:01:25.203 --> 1:01:27.988
Benny lets me and Jack come
over here on Sundays.

1:01:28.162 --> 1:01:31.949
I get to make him one.
You're really good with him.

1:01:32.123 --> 1:01:32.993
He's my buddy.

1:01:33.167 --> 1:01:34.473
No, I'm serious.

1:01:34.647 --> 1:01:36.518
What you're doing for your
brother, that's...

1:01:37.084 --> 1:01:38.695
that's really special.

1:01:41.610 --> 1:01:42.873
Well, he's the one defending
our country.

1:01:43.047 --> 1:01:44.875
It's the least I could do.

1:01:45.049 --> 1:01:47.094
No, it's not.

1:01:47.268 --> 1:01:49.836
Not many people would make
that kind of sacrifice.

1:01:52.447 --> 1:01:55.015
Yeah... you know, for a while...

1:01:55.189 --> 1:01:57.975
I didn't really know what
I wanted to do with my life.

1:01:58.149 --> 1:01:59.759
I was bouncing around
a little bit.

1:01:59.933 --> 1:02:02.544
I had a bartending gig
in Nashville.

1:02:02.719 --> 1:02:08.028
I got a guitar, played a few
open mic nights.

1:02:08.202 --> 1:02:09.813
Were you any good?

1:02:09.987 --> 1:02:11.728
No.

1:02:17.559 --> 1:02:18.909
But it was starting to feel
comfortable...

1:02:19.083 --> 1:02:21.738
starting to feel like home.

1:02:21.912 --> 1:02:23.870
But that's when Steve called
and I knew I had to come back.

1:02:26.525 --> 1:02:28.832
Do you ever miss it?
Your old life?

1:02:33.837 --> 1:02:34.794
No.

1:02:36.535 --> 1:02:39.451
I finally feel like I'm where
I'm supposed to be.

1:02:42.584 --> 1:02:45.892
I guess you don't always have
to go looking for what you need.

1:02:46.066 --> 1:02:48.460
Sometimes it finds you.

1:02:58.252 --> 1:02:59.819
How's that shake?
It's really good.

1:02:59.993 --> 1:03:00.907
Not bad.

1:03:06.347 --> 1:03:09.742
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:03:14.094 --> 1:03:15.487
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

1:03:17.445 --> 1:03:19.926
Here?
Absolutely.

1:03:20.100 --> 1:03:21.798
Why not?

1:03:27.412 --> 1:03:28.848
There's tables in the way.

1:03:30.763 --> 1:03:31.808
You're right.

1:03:37.291 --> 1:03:38.815
There's another one.

1:03:45.473 --> 1:03:47.084
Now, I know you didn't
miss me...

1:03:47.258 --> 1:03:51.784
but... you can't tell me
you didn't miss home.

1:03:51.958 --> 1:03:53.612
I have.

1:03:55.222 --> 1:03:57.964
And I may have missed you
a little, too...

1:03:58.138 --> 1:03:59.139
despite my better judgment.

1:03:59.313 --> 1:04:02.273
Of course, of course.

1:04:02.447 --> 1:04:06.103
♪ Will I ever see
the sun again ♪

1:04:06.277 --> 1:04:09.802
♪ You're the one
I can't get over ♪

1:04:12.805 --> 1:04:16.200
♪ I miss you
in a thousand ways ♪

1:04:16.374 --> 1:04:18.637
♪ Living every single day

1:04:18.811 --> 1:04:22.946
♪ You know I can't go lower

1:04:26.601 --> 1:04:30.040
Delivered safe and sound
just like I had promised.

1:04:30.214 --> 1:04:32.956
I had a really nice night.

1:04:33.130 --> 1:04:34.871
You mind if I get
that in writing.

1:04:41.268 --> 1:04:42.182
What do you know?

1:04:42.356 --> 1:04:44.968
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:04:53.019 --> 1:04:56.196
Oh, sorry! I saw headlights.

1:04:56.370 --> 1:04:58.155
It's okay, we were just
about to head in.

1:04:58.329 --> 1:05:00.070
How's Jack?

1:05:00.244 --> 1:05:02.899
Out like a light on the couch.

1:05:03.073 --> 1:05:03.900
I'll grab him.

1:05:08.034 --> 1:05:10.167
Subtle.

1:05:10.341 --> 1:05:12.909
I believe it was your
suggestion.

1:05:14.736 --> 1:05:17.957
Thank you, Caroline.
Mm... anytime.

1:05:18.131 --> 1:05:20.917
Well, see you tomorrow.

1:05:30.535 --> 1:05:34.017
I don't know, it was... nice.

1:05:34.191 --> 1:05:37.107
Nice is good.
Nice is strange.

1:05:37.281 --> 1:05:38.847
Why strange?

1:05:39.022 --> 1:05:41.720
I just never thought
I'd consider...

1:05:41.894 --> 1:05:44.288
opening that door again.

1:05:44.462 --> 1:05:46.246
And you're considering it now?

1:05:46.420 --> 1:05:49.336
Maybe?

1:05:49.510 --> 1:05:54.951
I don't know... it felt...
right.

1:05:59.912 --> 1:06:03.916
[ PHONE RINGS ]

1:06:04.090 --> 1:06:05.787
Hello.

1:06:05.962 --> 1:06:08.355
Holly! Turns out the race is a
little tighter than I thought.

1:06:08.529 --> 1:06:10.792
Lopez was in the office today...

1:06:10.967 --> 1:06:12.881
I think she impressed a lot
of people.

1:06:13.056 --> 1:06:15.145
Okay, is there anything
I can do?

1:06:15.319 --> 1:06:16.755
Bates is leaving town the day
after Christmas...

1:06:16.929 --> 1:06:18.235
to go on vacation.

1:06:18.409 --> 1:06:19.888
If you can get back here
in the next few days...

1:06:20.063 --> 1:06:21.194
I can get you some face
time with him...

1:06:21.368 --> 1:06:23.283
I think it could seal the deal.

1:06:23.457 --> 1:06:25.546
On Christmas Eve?

1:06:25.720 --> 1:06:27.331
If you really want the job,
I think the smart thing...

1:06:27.505 --> 1:06:29.246
to do is to get on the next
flight out.

1:06:29.420 --> 1:06:31.117
The window is closing,
let me know.

1:06:35.730 --> 1:06:37.994
Why don't I get us
some more pie.

1:06:49.179 --> 1:06:54.358
So, what are you going to do?

1:06:54.532 --> 1:06:57.361
I have to go back, right?

1:06:57.535 --> 1:07:00.016
You're asking me?

1:07:02.975 --> 1:07:07.371
I'd miss Christmas...
and the light show.

1:07:07.545 --> 1:07:14.247
And then there's Mike and
Jack... I don't know.

1:07:14.421 --> 1:07:18.034
You need to do whatever it takes
to make sure they choose you.

1:07:21.733 --> 1:07:24.083
That is... if it's still
what you want.

1:07:24.257 --> 1:07:27.043
Mom, I'd be crazy
to turn this down.

1:07:29.480 --> 1:07:32.178
Well then, sounds like you've
made up your mind.

1:07:35.094 --> 1:07:36.182
Yeah.

1:07:57.116 --> 1:07:58.422
Hey.

1:07:58.596 --> 1:08:00.337
Hey.
I didn't know--

1:08:00.511 --> 1:08:02.208
I meant to tell you, I talked
to Benny and I got him...

1:08:02.382 --> 1:08:04.950
to reserve you and Jack two
of the best seats...

1:08:05.124 --> 1:08:07.431
for tomorrow night's show...
right in there front.

1:08:07.605 --> 1:08:11.174
Actually, I-- I need to talk
to you about that.

1:08:11.348 --> 1:08:12.392
What's up?

1:08:12.566 --> 1:08:14.829
Okay, well--

1:08:15.003 --> 1:08:16.266
So, last night, I got a call--

1:08:16.440 --> 1:08:19.182
Mike! I'm sorry, Holly.

1:08:19.356 --> 1:08:21.227
I need to steal this guy
for a second.

1:08:21.401 --> 1:08:22.968
Look, we need you down
at festival site.

1:08:23.142 --> 1:08:24.535
I think the gingerbread house
got unloaded...

1:08:24.709 --> 1:08:26.406
in the wrong spot,
that's one heavy cookie.

1:08:26.580 --> 1:08:29.409
Okay, uh...

1:08:29.583 --> 1:08:30.758
Go, take care of it.

1:08:30.932 --> 1:08:32.586
You sure? I'm sorry.

1:08:32.760 --> 1:08:34.458
No, it's okay, we'll talk
tonight at dinner.

1:08:34.632 --> 1:08:36.112
Okay.

1:08:37.809 --> 1:08:41.073
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:08:45.860 --> 1:08:47.384
Ready?
Yes.

1:08:47.558 --> 1:08:50.256
Okay, knives, you're gonna chop.
Okay.

1:08:50.430 --> 1:08:53.259
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:09:38.391 --> 1:09:39.958
Perfect.

1:09:42.003 --> 1:09:43.875
[ DOOR BELL RINGS ]

1:09:51.926 --> 1:09:54.407
Hi.
Hi.

1:09:54.581 --> 1:09:57.018
Hi! Merry Christmas Eve-Eve!

1:09:57.193 --> 1:10:00.065
Well, don't you look festive.
Come on in.

1:10:06.898 --> 1:10:09.335
Holly's father always started
dinner with a prayer...

1:10:09.509 --> 1:10:12.251
so, Jack, would you like
to do the honors?

1:10:16.821 --> 1:10:19.345
Thank you for this meal
we are about to receive.

1:10:19.519 --> 1:10:22.609
Thank you for Uncle Mike...
thank you for Holly...

1:10:22.783 --> 1:10:25.482
and thank you for Miss Caroline.

1:10:25.656 --> 1:10:28.615
And please watch over my dad
until he gets home.

1:10:28.789 --> 1:10:31.444
Amen.
[CAROLINE] Amen.

1:10:31.618 --> 1:10:34.447
Amen. This looks fantastic.

1:10:34.621 --> 1:10:36.362
Oh, Holly helped.

1:10:36.536 --> 1:10:38.234
Holly mostly watched.

1:10:40.888 --> 1:10:42.586
How are things going
down at the festival?

1:10:42.760 --> 1:10:43.500
Well, your daughter built the
world's greatest...

1:10:43.674 --> 1:10:45.545
concession stand.

1:10:45.719 --> 1:10:48.418
I mean, I'd deny it,
but that would be a lie.

1:10:48.592 --> 1:10:51.551
Well, everyone I've talked to
is so excited for the show.

1:10:51.725 --> 1:10:55.381
I can't wait to see it again
after all these years.

1:10:55.555 --> 1:10:56.643
It's gonna be really
special, Mom.

1:10:56.817 --> 1:10:59.255
I hope so, this town needs it.

1:11:01.387 --> 1:11:02.432
Hey, Holly, guess what?

1:11:02.606 --> 1:11:03.650
What?

1:11:03.824 --> 1:11:05.652
My dad said whenever
he gets home...

1:11:05.826 --> 1:11:07.393
he's gonna take me
to Ship Island.

1:11:07.567 --> 1:11:08.960
Really?

1:11:09.134 --> 1:11:10.701
Yeah, Steve's buddy is out
of town until the New Year...

1:11:10.875 --> 1:11:13.573
said we could use his boat, pack
a lunch, make a whole day of it.

1:11:13.747 --> 1:11:15.314
Oh, that's so cool,
I'm so jealous.

1:11:19.057 --> 1:11:20.580
You don't have to be.

1:11:20.754 --> 1:11:22.278
We'd like you to come along.

1:11:32.592 --> 1:11:34.202
How could I say no?

1:11:50.654 --> 1:11:52.264
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1:11:56.747 --> 1:11:59.097
Wondering where you snuck
off to.

1:12:02.622 --> 1:12:03.362
Everything okay?

1:12:05.538 --> 1:12:09.412
Yeah, I'm just trying to figure
out how I tell you this.

1:12:09.586 --> 1:12:11.327
Tell me what?

1:12:13.894 --> 1:12:17.333
I have to leave tomorrow...
to go back to Los Angeles.

1:12:18.856 --> 1:12:21.206
Like an assignment?

1:12:21.380 --> 1:12:24.514
This magazine that I've done
some freelance work for...

1:12:24.688 --> 1:12:26.820
in the past is hiring a new
photo editor...

1:12:26.994 --> 1:12:30.433
and they're considering me
for the job.

1:12:33.174 --> 1:12:36.656
Wow. That sounds like a pretty,
big deal.

1:12:36.830 --> 1:12:38.354
It would be, yeah.

1:12:40.007 --> 1:12:41.313
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1:12:43.097 --> 1:12:44.403
Hey, bud.
Uncle Mike!

1:12:44.577 --> 1:12:45.491
Yeah.
Can I give it to her?

1:12:47.145 --> 1:12:48.364
Absolutely.

1:12:50.714 --> 1:12:52.237
Merry Christmas.

1:12:54.065 --> 1:12:56.981
Thank you. I love it.

1:12:57.155 --> 1:13:00.898
You're welcome.

1:13:01.072 --> 1:13:05.642
Hey! I brought you some turkey,
stuffing and some extra cobbler.

1:13:05.816 --> 1:13:08.514
You're the best, thank you.
Aw...

1:13:08.688 --> 1:13:10.386
Goodnight!
Goodnight.

1:13:12.083 --> 1:13:13.650
Are you leaving?

1:13:13.824 --> 1:13:17.349
Yeah, gotta get this guy to bed,
we have a big day tomorrow, so--

1:13:17.523 --> 1:13:19.395
Right.

1:13:22.963 --> 1:13:24.835
Hey, Jack, do me a favor, bud,
will you take this to the truck?

1:13:25.009 --> 1:13:26.053
I'll be there in a second, okay?
Yes, sir.

1:13:26.227 --> 1:13:28.360
Thank you for my present.
You're welcome.

1:13:35.759 --> 1:13:36.760
So no light show.

1:13:36.934 --> 1:13:41.808
No light show.

1:13:41.982 --> 1:13:45.116
I really wanted to be there.

1:13:47.727 --> 1:13:48.424
I know you did.

1:13:51.992 --> 1:13:53.733
Sounds like a great opportunity.

1:13:53.907 --> 1:13:57.433
I'm really happy for you...
congratulations.

1:14:06.920 --> 1:14:08.444
I guess this is goodbye.

1:14:19.977 --> 1:14:21.587
I'm gonna miss you.

1:14:21.761 --> 1:14:24.416
Stay in touch this time.

1:14:24.590 --> 1:14:26.374
I will.

1:14:34.774 --> 1:14:35.645
Merry Christmas.

1:14:35.819 --> 1:14:37.473
Merry Christmas.

1:14:39.170 --> 1:14:41.607
[ SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:15:17.643 --> 1:15:18.688
Do you have everything?

1:15:18.862 --> 1:15:20.516
I think so.

1:15:20.690 --> 1:15:23.475
Could you hang on to Prancer for
me? In case someone claims him?

1:15:23.649 --> 1:15:27.305
Of course, kinda grown attached
to the little guy.

1:15:29.002 --> 1:15:30.526
Come on.

1:15:34.094 --> 1:15:36.401
You know, Mom, you don't have
to drive me to the airport.

1:15:36.575 --> 1:15:38.838
I know you have a lot
of work to do for tonight.

1:15:39.012 --> 1:15:42.712
It's Christmas Eve and I am
going to spend every second...

1:15:42.886 --> 1:15:44.583
that I can with you and that's
the end of it.

1:15:44.757 --> 1:15:47.325
[ PHONE RINGS ]
Oh.

1:15:48.587 --> 1:15:49.675
Hello?

1:15:51.372 --> 1:15:55.333
Sure. Yeah, of course!

1:15:55.507 --> 1:15:58.205
Yes! I can meet you there.

1:15:58.379 --> 1:16:01.252
Okay, bye-bye.

1:16:04.777 --> 1:16:06.518
Slight change of plans.

1:16:11.697 --> 1:16:13.046
Hey, have you seen Holly?

1:16:13.220 --> 1:16:14.526
We're getting ready to move her
stand out into the park.

1:16:14.700 --> 1:16:16.963
Should we wait?
Nah, it's crunch time.

1:16:17.137 --> 1:16:18.791
You mind setting it up? I don't
think she's gonna mind.

1:16:18.965 --> 1:16:20.227
All right, you got it,
boss man.

1:16:20.401 --> 1:16:22.273
Thank you.

1:16:25.755 --> 1:16:28.714
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:16:43.860 --> 1:16:47.733
Excuse me, I think this guy
may belong to you.

1:16:47.907 --> 1:16:49.561
Thank you.

1:16:51.258 --> 1:16:53.565
Thank you so much
for coming down here.

1:16:53.739 --> 1:16:58.004
You have saved my
granddaughter's Christmas.

1:16:58.178 --> 1:16:59.832
I'm just glad it actually
worked out.

1:17:00.006 --> 1:17:01.573
It was kind of a shot
in the dark.

1:17:01.747 --> 1:17:03.662
Can I buy you lunch?
It's the least I can do.

1:17:03.836 --> 1:17:05.533
I have a plane to catch,
but thank you.

1:17:05.708 --> 1:17:08.319
Okay, then next time
you're in town.

1:17:12.410 --> 1:17:13.803
You own this place?

1:17:13.977 --> 1:17:15.979
I do, have you stayed with us?

1:17:16.153 --> 1:17:18.895
No, I haven't, but I heard all
about what you did...

1:17:19.069 --> 1:17:21.637
for Gulfport, after the
hurricane.

1:17:21.811 --> 1:17:24.596
Well, this town is close to my
heart. I grew up here.

1:17:24.770 --> 1:17:26.859
Really?

1:17:27.033 --> 1:17:30.907
Yeah, I was halfway around the
world when the storm hit and...

1:17:31.081 --> 1:17:32.865
tell you the truth, I hadn't
thought of this little town...

1:17:33.039 --> 1:17:36.826
in ages, but when I saw those
pictures of what had happened...

1:17:37.000 --> 1:17:40.046
I knew I had to do something.

1:17:40.220 --> 1:17:43.006
There was one in particular
of this-- of this mother...

1:17:43.180 --> 1:17:46.618
holding her little baby and
she's about the age...

1:17:46.792 --> 1:17:49.752
of my granddaughter at the time
and, well, she had this look...

1:17:49.926 --> 1:17:52.450
of determination in the middle
of all this destruction.

1:17:52.624 --> 1:17:54.104
I won't forget that.

1:17:54.278 --> 1:17:57.020
I called our developer
that night.

1:17:57.194 --> 1:17:59.892
All because you saw a photo?

1:18:00.066 --> 1:18:03.461
Well, even though I was halfway
around the world...

1:18:06.986 --> 1:18:08.509
for that moment, it just took
me back home...

1:18:08.684 --> 1:18:10.468
and now I am here to stay.

1:18:12.426 --> 1:18:15.473
[ CHRISTMAS MUSIC FADES UP ]

1:18:36.059 --> 1:18:36.494
All right, what do you want
to do first, man?

1:18:36.668 --> 1:18:38.496
I wish my dad was here.

1:18:40.411 --> 1:18:41.499
Yeah, me, too.

1:18:42.543 --> 1:18:44.676
... and Holly.

1:18:46.025 --> 1:18:48.114
Me, too.

1:18:48.288 --> 1:18:50.421
What did you want me to do,
ask her to stay?

1:18:57.515 --> 1:18:59.865
You're right, I should have
asked her to stay.

1:19:02.215 --> 1:19:03.739
Come on.

1:19:18.536 --> 1:19:19.885
Evening, everyone.

1:19:20.059 --> 1:19:21.234
Hi, Mr. McGuire!

1:19:21.408 --> 1:19:23.671
Didn't Caroline do
a fabulous job?

1:19:23.846 --> 1:19:27.153
Aw...
Of course, knew she would.

1:19:27.327 --> 1:19:30.896
So, uh, any recommendations?

1:19:31.070 --> 1:19:34.857
Well, the sticky buns seem
to be a big hit.

1:19:35.031 --> 1:19:37.555
Those do look good.

1:19:42.647 --> 1:19:47.608
Listen, Caroline, I feel like
I've made you uncomfortable.

1:19:47.783 --> 1:19:50.786
No... no, you didn't do
anything wrong.

1:19:53.353 --> 1:19:55.791
I was-- I was flattered.

1:19:59.490 --> 1:20:02.623
Well, I hope we can
still be friends?

1:20:02.798 --> 1:20:04.756
Sure would hate to lose
my best customer.

1:20:04.930 --> 1:20:06.714
Of course.

1:20:06.889 --> 1:20:08.499
Great.

1:20:10.501 --> 1:20:13.809
No... it's on me.

1:20:15.462 --> 1:20:17.116
Thank you.

1:20:17.290 --> 1:20:20.424
Well... enjoy the show.

1:20:20.598 --> 1:20:21.947
You, too.

1:20:38.572 --> 1:20:41.532
[ CHRISTMAS MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:20:51.368 --> 1:20:53.109
Alright. Hello Gulfport.

1:21:00.420 --> 1:21:02.553
I just want to welcome everyone
to the annual...

1:21:02.727 --> 1:21:04.294
Harbor Lights Festival.

1:21:04.468 --> 1:21:07.645
First, a huge round of applause
for all of our volunteers.

1:21:13.129 --> 1:21:14.695
Without their hard work,
we can't do this.

1:21:14.870 --> 1:21:17.916
And a huge thank you
to Mayor Billy Hughes...

1:21:18.090 --> 1:21:19.744
and the city for all
of their support.

1:21:25.793 --> 1:21:28.666
I think we all know why this
year's festival is so special.

1:21:31.582 --> 1:21:32.888
Five years ago, our community
was thrown quite a curveball...

1:21:36.674 --> 1:21:38.067
and we didn't let it beat us...

1:21:38.241 --> 1:21:41.200
and we got through it
side-by-side...

1:21:41.374 --> 1:21:44.203
Holly!
Hey!

1:21:44.377 --> 1:21:46.597
...because we're a family.

1:21:55.214 --> 1:21:56.128
And what better time
to celebrate family...

1:21:56.302 --> 1:21:57.695
than at Christmas?

1:22:00.437 --> 1:22:02.178
So, if you haven't already,
please grab a spot on the lawn.

1:22:02.352 --> 1:22:06.922
Grab a chair, and since it's
actually a tad chilly tonight.

1:22:07.096 --> 1:22:10.099
Cozy up with your loved one,
sit back and relax.

1:22:10.273 --> 1:22:11.622
Enjoy the show.

1:22:22.894 --> 1:22:25.157
Let there be light.

1:22:25.331 --> 1:22:28.639
[ MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:22:55.579 --> 1:23:02.934
♪ Silent night Holy night

1:23:05.197 --> 1:23:12.857
♪ Shepherds pray
at the sight ♪

1:23:15.555 --> 1:23:22.910
♪ Glory streams
from heaven afar ♪

1:23:23.085 --> 1:23:25.957
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

1:24:01.558 --> 1:24:04.039
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:24:18.444 --> 1:24:20.055
Great show, captain.

1:24:26.278 --> 1:24:27.975
Shouldn't you be on an airplane?

1:24:29.847 --> 1:24:33.068
Yeah, well, I uh,
I turned down the job.

1:24:36.419 --> 1:24:38.029
Really?
Yeah.

1:24:38.203 --> 1:24:40.945
I uh... I decided I didn't
want to give this up.

1:24:41.119 --> 1:24:42.251
The security would have
been nice...

1:24:42.425 --> 1:24:45.167
and the money would have been
nicer, but...

1:24:45.341 --> 1:24:48.257
I'm meant to be behind
the camera.

1:24:48.431 --> 1:24:51.042
You know, all I've ever wanted
is to make a difference...

1:24:51.216 --> 1:24:56.613
a real difference, and this
is how I can do it.

1:24:56.787 --> 1:24:59.050
I talked to my old editor and I
pitched him a new series...

1:24:59.224 --> 1:25:02.358
about Gulfport's recovery,
and he loved it.

1:25:02.532 --> 1:25:05.143
This town can inspire a lot
of people...

1:25:05.317 --> 1:25:07.102
and I want to be a part of that.

1:25:09.539 --> 1:25:12.498
And I want to do that...
with you.

1:25:12.672 --> 1:25:15.893
[ SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES ]

1:25:17.938 --> 1:25:21.899
[JACK] Uncle Mike! Holly!
Santa's here! Come on!

1:25:34.955 --> 1:25:37.132
Ho! Ho! Ho!
Merry Christmas!

1:25:38.742 --> 1:25:41.136
Everyone, please, please
gather around.

1:25:47.794 --> 1:25:50.362
Hello, hello. Nice to meet you.
How are you?

1:25:50.536 --> 1:25:53.322
Excuse me. Excuse me!
Ho! Ho! Ho! Merry Christmas!

1:25:53.496 --> 1:25:56.542
Excuse me, excuse me. Thank you.

1:25:56.716 --> 1:25:58.370
Oh! Well hi there.

1:25:58.544 --> 1:26:01.460
[SANTA]
Ho! Ho! Ho! Merry Christmas!

1:26:01.634 --> 1:26:04.289
He gets quite a lot of volume.

1:26:04.463 --> 1:26:07.945
I think his ho-ho-ho might
put mine to shame.

1:26:08.119 --> 1:26:12.471
Mr. Kriss? Wait, if you're
here...

1:26:12.645 --> 1:26:15.344
Who's in the suit?

1:26:15.518 --> 1:26:18.564
Hey! You're not Mr. Kriss.

1:26:18.738 --> 1:26:24.179
No, Jack... I'm not.

1:26:26.268 --> 1:26:27.878
Dad!

1:26:29.923 --> 1:26:31.925
Steve? How did he get here?

1:26:32.099 --> 1:26:35.059
I may have called in a favor.

1:26:41.021 --> 1:26:43.415
Hey, man, how you doing?

1:26:43.589 --> 1:26:45.287
I've got some great news, Jack.

1:26:45.461 --> 1:26:48.899
I've been reassigned
to a base nearby.

1:26:50.770 --> 1:26:52.903
So you're staying? For good?

1:26:54.121 --> 1:26:55.210
For good, Jack.

1:27:10.529 --> 1:27:12.096
Not bad, huh?

1:27:12.270 --> 1:27:15.491
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

1:27:15.665 --> 1:27:20.931
[ CHRISTMAS RINGTONE
SOUNDING ]

1:27:24.326 --> 1:27:25.588
Yes, dear.

1:27:25.762 --> 1:27:28.199
Oh, ho, no, I'm on my way now.

1:27:28.373 --> 1:27:32.377
I uh-- I had an early gift
to deliver.

1:27:32.551 --> 1:27:37.252
Well... it's gonna be
a wonderful night!

1:27:37.426 --> 1:27:40.472
Uh-huh, but you don't have
to wait up, as usual.

1:27:40.646 --> 1:27:42.953
I'll see you then.

1:27:55.052 --> 1:27:56.271
Ho! Ho! Ho!

1:27:56.445 --> 1:27:59.448
That one wasn't so bad.

1:27:59.622 --> 1:28:02.102
Ho! Ho! Ho!

1:28:02.277 --> 1:28:05.062
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:28:08.674 --> 1:28:10.894
So, you glad you stayed?

1:28:11.068 --> 1:28:13.244
Yeah. I am.

1:28:15.028 --> 1:28:16.291
What now?

1:28:18.597 --> 1:28:20.295
Well, I was planning
on kissing you.

1:28:26.170 --> 1:28:29.216
[ MUSIC FADES UP ]

1:28:35.919 --> 1:28:36.876
Here, let me.

1:28:37.050 --> 1:28:38.617
Thanks, sweetie.

1:28:38.791 --> 1:28:39.879
Uh-uh, I got it,
I got it.

1:28:40.053 --> 1:28:41.141
I can carry one.

1:28:41.316 --> 1:28:42.708
I know, but you don't
have to.

1:28:42.882 --> 1:28:45.058
Well, it looks like you've run
out of hands, so--

1:28:45.232 --> 1:28:47.713
I'll just take this one, thanks!
Wait, is it too heavy?

1:28:47.887 --> 1:28:49.324
You can rest if you need to!

1:28:53.284 --> 1:28:55.591
Whew! This one?

1:28:55.765 --> 1:28:59.116
Yep... thanks.
There you go.

1:28:59.290 --> 1:29:01.423
Any special requests
for Christmas dinner?

1:29:01.597 --> 1:29:04.034
Hm... peach cobbler.

1:29:04.208 --> 1:29:05.514
Ah! You got it.

1:29:05.688 --> 1:29:07.516
My dad bought the turkey
last night.

1:29:07.690 --> 1:29:11.215
He says that I can help him
whenever he deep fries it.

1:29:11.389 --> 1:29:13.173
Do me a favor? Will you guys
grab these bows...

1:29:13.348 --> 1:29:16.742
and hit the concession stand
with them? Thank you, thank you.

1:29:16.916 --> 1:29:20.093
Hey, Allison? Yeah, yeah,
right by the tree.

1:29:20.267 --> 1:29:21.486
Thank you.

1:29:23.401 --> 1:29:25.708
Guess who?

1:29:25.882 --> 1:29:27.057
Betty?

1:29:27.231 --> 1:29:29.146
I'm never gonna live that down,
am I?

1:29:29.320 --> 1:29:30.669
You're not supposed to be back
for three hours.

1:29:30.843 --> 1:29:31.931
What are you doing?

1:29:32.105 --> 1:29:33.629
Oh, I gave you a conservative
estimate.

1:29:33.803 --> 1:29:35.370
Helps with the whole surprise
thing.

1:29:35.544 --> 1:29:36.762
How was Paris?

1:29:36.936 --> 1:29:38.547
It was great! But I'm really
glad to be home.

1:29:38.721 --> 1:29:42.028
Oh... I got you something.

1:29:42.202 --> 1:29:44.596
Please be croissants.
Please be croissants.

1:29:44.770 --> 1:29:47.556
Sadly, they don't travel well.

1:29:47.730 --> 1:29:50.341
Holly!
Hey, Jack!

1:29:50.515 --> 1:29:52.604
So, Jack has been working
on the banner.

1:29:52.778 --> 1:29:57.174
No better man for the job.
Thanks.

1:29:57.348 --> 1:30:00.133
Should we show her?
Now?

1:30:01.483 --> 1:30:03.702
Why not?
Okay.

1:30:05.269 --> 1:30:08.403
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:30:22.982 --> 1:30:24.070
Oh--

1:30:28.466 --> 1:30:30.599
Um, it's a miscommunication...

1:30:30.773 --> 1:30:32.862
we didn't have time
for a trial run.

1:30:34.385 --> 1:30:36.953
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

1:30:46.179 --> 1:30:49.444
This has been the best year
of my life.

1:30:49.618 --> 1:30:52.621
And I know there's a person
out there for everyone...

1:30:52.795 --> 1:30:55.754
and for me, it's you.

1:30:59.628 --> 1:31:00.759
Of course, had you been here
two hours later...

1:31:00.933 --> 1:31:03.153
there'd be a string quartet
and six dozen roses.

1:31:08.463 --> 1:31:12.771
The second I saw you, I knew I
couldn't wait one more moment...

1:31:12.945 --> 1:31:15.470
to ask you to be my wife.

1:31:22.564 --> 1:31:24.479
So, will you?

1:31:26.524 --> 1:31:27.830
Yes.

1:31:41.626 --> 1:31:42.497
Come here.

1:31:45.543 --> 1:31:46.892
I love you.
I love you.

1:31:47.066 --> 1:31:48.459
I can't believe you
did all this.

1:31:48.633 --> 1:31:50.330
All I got you is
an Eifel Tower tie.

1:31:50.505 --> 1:31:51.810
I can wear it for the wedding.

1:31:54.160 --> 1:31:55.510
Welcome to the family!

1:32:00.340 --> 1:32:02.429
Hey, bud.
Yes!

1:32:02.604 --> 1:32:03.866
Congrats.

1:32:05.607 --> 1:32:06.651
You gettin' married.

1:32:06.825 --> 1:32:07.870
Yeah.

1:32:08.044 --> 1:32:09.393
Love is beautiful.

1:32:11.264 --> 1:32:14.093
You guys, we got a show to do!
Back to work!

1:32:16.400 --> 1:32:18.794
[ CHRISTMAS MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:32:25.583 --> 1:32:28.412
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

1:32:36.463 --> 1:32:38.901
♪ Looking for my baby

1:32:39.075 --> 1:32:42.905
♪ Searching high
and looking low ♪

1:32:43.079 --> 1:32:46.473
♪ Oh been looking
for my baby this Christmas ♪

1:32:46.648 --> 1:32:48.780
♪ Just gotta let her know

1:32:51.696 --> 1:32:56.309
♪ All I want for Christmas
is to keep her from the cold ♪

1:32:59.051 --> 1:33:00.879
♪ Yeah I been rolling
on the river ♪

1:33:01.053 --> 1:33:03.012
♪ Been travelling
through the pines ♪

1:33:03.186 --> 1:33:06.885
♪ Been checking out the hills
and the beautiful coastline ♪

1:33:07.059 --> 1:33:09.453
♪ It's a Mississippi
Christmas ♪

1:33:09.627 --> 1:33:12.499
♪ All the family's gathered
round ♪

1:33:14.284 --> 1:33:16.939
♪ Yeah it's Christmas
in the Southland ♪

1:33:17.113 --> 1:33:19.594
♪ See the lights and hear
the sounds ♪
